n of employment + 8 years\n + Payslips (Employee Copies): Retained for the duration of employment + 8 years	2026-04-09 15:14:17.964285
1f8c337d-1551-407a-a766-c8cfe8623866	45329294-9b72-4167-92a0-a18b814928b7	1	What is the leave policy?	Our organization offers a comprehensive leave policy to support the well-being and work-life balance of our employees. \n\n**Paid Time Off (PTO)**: Employees are entitled to accrue a certain number of paid days off per year, which can be used for vacation, sick leave, or personal days. The accrual rate is as follows:\n- 10 days per year for full-time employees (pro-rated for part-time employees)\n- 5 days per year for probationary employees (first 6 months of employment)\n\n**Annual Leave**: Employees can take up to 15 days of annual leave per year, which can be used for vacation or personal reasons. Annual leave must be requested and approved in advance.\n\n**Sick Leave**: Employees are entitled to take paid sick leave for up to 5 days per year. If an employee exceeds this limit, they will be placed on unpaid leave.\n\n**Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA)**: Our organization offers up to 12 weeks of unpaid leave under the FMLA for eligible employees, which includes bonding with a new child, caring for a family member with a serious health condition, or taking leave due to a serious health condition.\n\n**Bereavement Leave**: Employees are entitled to up to 3 days of bereavement leave for the death of an immediate family member.\n\n**Holiday Leave**: Our organization observes 10 paid holidays per year, which include New Year's Day, Memorial Day, Independence Day, Labor Day, Thanksgiving Day, and Christmas Day.\n\n**Jury Duty Leave**: Employees are entitled to take paid leave for jury duty, but must provide documentation from the court.\n\n**Military Leave**: Our organization offers up to 26 weeks of unpaid leave for employees who are called to active duty.\n\n**Leave of Absence**: Employees may be eligible for a leave of absence in certain circumstances, such as a disability leave or a leave for a family member. The specifics of this policy will be discussed on a case-by-case basis.\n\n**Leave Request Process**: Employees must submit a leave request form to their supervisor or HR representative at least 2 weeks in advance, except for emergencies or unexpected situations. Requests will be approved or denied based on business needs and availability.\n\nPlease note that this is a general overview of our leave policy, and specific details may vary depending on individual circumstances. If you have any questions or concerns, please reach out to your supervisor or HR representative.	2026-04-09 09:44:28.407523
