bc66cff8-afc7-4697-bf10-a85ecc0cb0b9	5f9edd8b-1a51-47a3-91b3-76d305f4b287	24	Explain leave policy	**Leave Policy Overview**\n\nAt Artemis Technology Limited, we understand the importance of providing our employees with a balance between work and personal life. Our Leave Policy aims to support employees in managing their time off, whether for medical reasons, family emergencies, or personal needs.\n\n**Types of Leave**\n\nWe offer the following types of leave:\n\n1. **Long-term Illness**: Eligible employees can take up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period for medical and family reasons, as per the U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act.\n2. **Bereavement Leave**: We provide support and time off for employees to cope with the loss of a loved one.\n3. **Other Leave Types**: Our Leave Policy also covers other types of leave, including:\n * Leave Travel Allowance (LTA)\n * Travel reimbursement during leave periods\n * Medical Allowance (fixed allowance towards medical expenses)\n * Provident Fund – Employer (employer's statutory contribution to PF)\n * Gratuity Provision (statutory retirement benefit accrual)\n\n**Eligibility and Conditions**\n\nTo be eligible for leave, employees must have worked for us for more than 12 months and have worked at least 1,250 hours within 12 months before their leave begins.\n\n**Deductions from Gross Salary**\n\nThe following statutory and voluntary deductions are applied before arriving at the net pay:\n\n1. **Provident Fund (PF) – Employee**: 12% of Basic Salary\n2. **Professional Tax (PT)**: State-specific statutory levy\n3. **Tax Deducted at Source (TDS)**: Income Tax Act – based on declared investments\n\n**Contact HR for More Information**\n\nIf you have any questions or need more information about our Leave Policy, please contact the HR Division.	2026-04-10 09:49:59.429189
