44ea2c6e-dc41-4ed7-8cb8-f1ad67be4029	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	3	what is leave policy?	**Concise Policy Summary**\n\n**Source:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n**Key Policies:**\n\n* **Employment Basics:**\n + Full-time employees: 30 hours/week or 130 hours/month\n + Part-time employees: fewer than 30 hours/week\n + Employment contract types: temporary or indefinite duration\n* **Workplace Policies:**\n + Confidentiality and data protection: protect private information about clients, employees, partners, and company\n + Non-compete and non-disclosure agreements (NDAs) for eligible employees\n* **Employee Benefits:**\n + Health insurance package (contact HR for more information)\n + COBRA: continue group health benefits after leaving the company (if applicable)\n* **Leave Policies:**\n + Sick leave: inform manager, use sick days, and rest for a day before returning to work\n + Long-term illness: 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave (U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act)\n + Bereavement leave: up to 2 months of unpaid leave extension\n + Parental leave: remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms\n* **Termination and Resignation:**\n + Employment is "at-will" in the U.S.\n + Progressive discipline process: 6 steps of increasing severity\n + Resignation: voluntary termination, 2 weeks' notice preferred (1 month's notice for highly specialized or executive positions)\n* **References:**\n + Laid-off employees may receive references\n + Resigned employees may ask for references, but manager has the right to oblige or refuse\n* **Policy Revision:**\n + Annual revision of the handbook to update with legislation and employment trends\n + Contact HR for policy revisions or updates	2026-04-10 12:16:40.037893
d29032d5-7369-4e37-ab9d-93a07fcae22c	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	4	what is leave policy?	**Concise Policy Summary**\n\n**Source:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n**Key Policy Areas:**\n\n* **Employment Basics:**\n + Full-time employees: 30 hours/week or 130 hours/month\n + Part-time employees: fewer than 30 hours/week\n + Employment contract types: temporary or indefinite duration\n* **Workplace Policies:**\n + Confidentiality and data protection: protect private information\n + Non-compete and non-disclosure agreements (NDAs)\n* **Employee Benefits:**\n + Health insurance package (contact HR for more information)\n + COBRA: continue group health benefits after leaving the company\n + Non-smoking and substance abuse policies\n* **Leave Policies:**\n + Sick leave: inform manager, use sick days, and rest for a day before returning to work\n + PTO: use for routine healthcare appointments\n + Long-term illness: 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave\n + Bereavement leave: up to 2 months of unpaid leave\n + Parental leave: remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms\n* **Leaving the Company:**\n + Resignation: inform HR or manager, 2 weeks' notice (highly specialized or executive positions: 1 month's notice)\n + Termination: "at-will" employment, progressive discipline process, and termination without warning for serious offenses\n* **Policy Revision:**\n + Annual revision of the handbook to update with legislation and employment trends\n\n**Eligibility and Exceptions:**\n\n* Eligible employees for health insurance package and COBRA\n* Eligible employees for long-term illness leave: 12 months of service and 1,250 hours worked in 12 months\n* Eligible employees for bereavement leave: up to 2 months of unpaid leave\n* Eligible employees for parental leave: remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms\n\n**Approval Flow:**\n\n* HR approval for COBRA and long-term illness leave\n* Manager approval for sick leave and PTO\n* HR approval for resignation and termination\n\n**Important Dates and Limits:**\n\n* 12 months of service for long-term illness leave\n* 1,250 hours worked in 12 months for long-term illness leave\n* 2 weeks' notice for resignation (highly specialized or executive positions: 1 month's notice)\n* Up to 2 months of unpaid bereavement leave\n* Annual revision of the handbook	2026-04-10 12:17:37.130805
