075e9ca5-9973-44ea-aece-ed4f9a52d845	5f9edd8b-1a51-47a3-91b3-76d305f4b287	40	explain leave policy	## Leave Policy\n\n### Overview\n\n- The leave policy at Artemis Technology Limited aims to provide employees with a fair and flexible system for taking time off from work.\n- The policy outlines the different types of leave available, eligibility criteria, and procedures for requesting leave.\n\n### Key Rules\n\n- **Types of Leave:**\n  - **Annual Leave:** Employees are entitled to a certain number of paid days off per year, depending on their employment contract.\n  - **Sick Leave:** Employees can take time off for medical reasons, and the company will provide a certain number of paid sick days per year.\n  - **Family and Medical Leave:** Employees are entitled to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period for medical and family reasons.\n  - **Bereavement Leave:** Employees can take time off to cope with the loss of a loved one.\n- **Eligibility Criteria:**\n  - Employees must have worked for the company for more than 12 months and have worked at least 1,250 hours within 12 months before their leave begins to be eligible for family and medical leave.\n- **Leave Request Procedure:**\n  - Employees must submit a leave request to their manager or HR department in advance, whenever possible.\n  - The company will review and approve or deny leave requests based on business needs and availability.\n\n### Process\n\n1. **Annual Leave:**\n  - Employees are entitled to a certain number of paid days off per year, depending on their employment contract.\n  - Employees must submit a leave request to their manager or HR department in advance, whenever possible.\n  - The company will review and approve or deny leave requests based on business needs and availability.\n2. **Sick Leave:**\n  - Employees can take time off for medical reasons, and the company will provide a certain number of paid sick days per year.\n  - Employees must submit a doctor's note or other documentation to support their sick leave request.\n  - The company will review and approve or deny sick leave requests based on business needs and availability.\n3. **Family and Medical Leave:**\n  - Employees are entitled to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period for medical and family reasons.\n  - Employees must submit a leave request to their manager or HR department in advance, whenever possible.\n  - The company will review and approve or deny leave requests based on business needs and availability.\n4. **Bereavement Leave:**\n  - Employees can take time off to cope with the loss of a loved one.\n  - Employees must submit a leave request to their manager or HR department in advance, whenever possible.\n  - The company will review and approve or deny leave requests based on business needs and availability.\n\n### Important Notes\n\n- **Leave Travel Allowance (LTA):** Employees are entitled to a certain amount of LTA per year, which can be used for travel expenses during leave periods.\n- **Travel Reimbursement:** Employees can claim reimbursement for travel expenses during leave periods, subject to certain conditions.\n- **Medical Allowance:** Employees are entitled to a fixed allowance towards medical expenses, which is taxable unless reimbursed with bills.\n- **Provident Fund – Employer:** The company contributes to the employee's Provident Fund, which is not included in gross salary and is part of the CTC.\n- **Gratuity Provision:** The company provides a statutory retirement benefit accrual, which is not included in gross salary and is part of the CTC.	2026-04-10 12:21:08.129364
