df6c252a-81d0-4cc6-a8e2-37037ef30c6c	5f9edd8b-1a51-47a3-91b3-76d305f4b287	52	give summary of payroll policy	**Payroll Policy Summary**\n\n**Scope:** This policy applies to all employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees of Artemis Technology Limited.\n\n**Key Principles:**\n\n1. **Accuracy & Timeliness:** Payroll data must be accurate and processed in a timely manner.\n2. **Transparency:** Employees will receive itemized payslips detailing all earnings, deductions, and net pay.\n3. **Equity & Non-Discrimination:** Payroll processes will be conducted in a fair and non-discriminatory manner.\n4. **Data Integrity:** Payroll records will be maintained securely and accurately.\n\n**Payroll Process:**\n\n1. **Raise a Query:** Employees can raise a query regarding payroll computation or concerns regarding deductions, reimbursements, or settlements.\n2. **Investigation:** The Payroll team will investigate the concern and provide a written response within 5 working days.\n3. **Escalation:** If the employee is not satisfied with the resolution, the matter may be escalated to the HR Business Partner and subsequently to the HR Head for final resolution.\n\n**Record Keeping:**\n\n* Monthly Payroll Register: Retained for 8 years after employment ends\n* Payslips (Employee Copies): Retained for 8 years after employment ends\n\n**Payroll Confidentiality:**\n\n* Payroll data constitutes sensitive personal and financial information.\n* Employees, managers, HR personnel, and Finance staff are bound by confidentiality obligations.\n* Breach of payroll confidentiality may attract disciplinary action.\n\n**Payroll Timelines:**\n\n* Salary disbursement: 29th of the current month\n* Payslip generation & distribution: 1st working day of the following month\n* Statutory filing (PF, ESI, PT, TDS): As per statutory due dates\n\n**Policy Review:**\n\n* The Payroll Policy will be reviewed annually or as necessitated by changes in applicable tax laws, labour regulations, statutory requirements, or organisational restructuring.	2026-04-10 14:54:19.405347
61cc8ae9-cfc0-4349-9075-ed46002a5d81	5f9edd8b-1a51-47a3-91b3-76d305f4b287	53	what is the culture at artemis?	**Culture at Artemis**\n\nAt Artemis, the culture is built around the following values:\n\n1. **Clarity**: Employees are expected to make their ideas understandable and actionable.\n2. **Collaboration**: Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\n3. **Accountability**: Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\n4. **Deliberate Communication**: Employees are expected to communicate clearly and effectively, both in writing and in person.\n5. **Respect**: Employees are expected to treat each other with respect and professionalism.\n\n**Key Principles**\n\n1. **Listen Carefully**: Employees are encouraged to listen carefully to each other and to clients.\n2. **Think Rigorously**: Employees are expected to think critically and rigorously, and to challenge assumptions.\n3. **Follow Through**: Employees are expected to follow through on commitments and to deliver high-quality work.\n\n**Work Environment**\n\nAt Artemis, the work environment is designed to support collaboration and productivity. Employees are encouraged to work together to achieve common goals, and to take ownership of their contributions.\n\n**Recognition**\n\nGood work is recognized through impact rather than visibility. Employees are encouraged to focus on delivering high-quality work that has a positive impact on the organization and its clients.\n\nOverall, the culture at Artemis is built around a commitment to excellence, collaboration, and accountability.	2026-04-10 14:57:28.738497
