c32f4a60-37b4-4075-981f-44c3b962f51b	e6547593-8058-4892-b512-729fabbc960d	4	explain payroll policy	**Payroll Policy Summary**\n\n**Document:** Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n1. **Purpose:** The Payroll Policy establishes a comprehensive framework for accurate, timely, and compliant processing of employee compensation.\n2. **Scope:** The policy applies to all full-time and part-time employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees.\n3. **Guiding Principles:**\n\t* Accuracy & Timeliness: Payroll calculations and disbursements will be processed accurately and within the defined payroll calendar.\n\t* Confidentiality: Payroll information is strictly confidential.\n\t* Compliance: Artemis Technology Limited will adhere to applicable labour laws, tax regulations, and statutory obligations.\n\t* Transparency: Employees will receive itemized payslips detailing all earnings, deductions, and net pay.\n\t* Equity & Non-Discrimination: Payroll processes will be conducted in a fair and non-discriminatory manner.\n\t* Data Integrity: All payroll records will be maintained securely and accurately.\n4. **Payroll Timelines:**\n\t* Salary disbursement: 29th of the current month\n\t* Payslip generation & distribution: Last working day of the month\n\t* Statutory filing (PF, ESI, PT, TDS): 1st working day of the following month\n5. **Payroll Inputs:**\n\t* New joiner details, separation details, approved increment letters, attendance records, and overtime claims.\n6. **Statutory Compliance & Deductions:**\n\t* Employees' Provident Fund (EPF)\n\t* Employee State Insurance (ESI)\n\t* Professional Tax (PT)\n\t* Tax Deducted at Source (TDS)\n\t* Labour Welfare Fund (LWF)\n\t* Gratuity (Accrual & Payment)\n7. **Salary Revision & Increment Process:**\n\t* Increment decisions are communicated by the HR team through official revision letters.\n\t* Revised salaries are effective from the date specified in the increment letter.\n8. **Payroll Confidentiality:**\n\t* Payroll data constitutes sensitive personal and financial information.\n\t* All employees, managers, HR personnel, and Finance staff are bound by confidentiality obligations.\n9. **Record Keeping:**\n\t* Monthly Payroll Register: Duration of employment + 8 years\n\t* Payslips (Employee Copies): Duration of employment + 8 years\n10. **Payroll Grievance Redressal:**\n\t* Employees can raise a formal grievance through the HR Operations / Payroll team.\n\t* The Payroll team will investigate the concern and provide a written response within 5 working days.\n\t* If the employee is not satisfied with the resolution, the matter may be escalated to the HR Business Partner and subsequently to the HR Head for final resolution.\n\n**Related Policies:**\n\n* Employee Handbook\n* Compensation & Benefits Policy\n* Leave Policy\n* Expense Reimbursement & Travel Policy\n* Separation & Exit Policy\n* Data Privacy & Confidentiality Policy\n* IT & Acceptable Use Policy\n* Disciplinary Policy (HR-DP-001)\n* Whistleblower Policy\n\nSources:\n- Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf	2026-04-13 16:15:26.704077
