cruitment does not have a formal grievance process, while Payroll has a specific process for addressing payroll-related concerns |\n| **Policy Review** | Not mentioned in the provided excerpt | Payroll Policy will be reviewed annually or upon significant changes | Both policies aim to maintain relevance and effectiveness | Recruitment does not have a formal review process, while Payroll has a regular review process |\n\n**Similarities:**\n\n* Both policies aim to maintain fairness and transparency\n* Both policies emphasize the importance of confidentiality\n* Both policies outline specific roles and responsibilities\n* Both policies aim to provide a fair and transparent process for addressing concerns\n\n**Differences:**\n\n* Objective: Recruitment focuses on hiring, while Payroll focuses on compensation and benefits\n* Scope: Recruitment is limited to hiring, while Payroll covers a broader range of compensation, benefits, and statutory requirements\n* Responsibilities: Recruitment responsibilities are limited to hiring, while Payroll responsibilities cover a broader range of tasks\n* Confidentiality: Recruitment confidentiality is limited to candidate data, while Payroll confidentiality covers a broader range of sensitive information\n* Grievance Redressal: Recruitment does not have a formal grievance process, while Payroll has a specific process for addressing payroll-related concerns\n* Policy Review: Recruitment does not have a formal review process, while Payroll has a regular review process\n\nSources:\n- Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n- artemis_recruitment_policy (1).pdf\n- ArtemisDisciplinaryPolicy (2).pdf\n- Artemis_IT_Security_Policy (1).pdf	2026-04-14 09:47:59.331078
