be63f6c3-a12c-4378-8f28-a671fb863e4c	fb52dfd8-ade8-4e45-b9b9-b817d8e006fc	5	summarize the payroll policy at artemis	**Payroll Policy Summary at Artemis Technology Limited**\n\n**Document:** Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n* **Scope:** The policy applies to all full-time and part-time employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees.\n* **Guiding Principles:**\n\t+ Accuracy & Timeliness: Payroll calculations and disbursements will be processed accurately and within the defined payroll calendar.\n\t+ Confidentiality: Payroll information is strictly confidential and shall not be disclosed to unauthorized individuals.\n\t+ Compliance: Artemis Technology Limited will adhere to applicable labour laws, tax regulations, and other statutory obligations.\n\t+ Transparency: The company will maintain transparency in payroll processes and timelines.\n* **Salary Structure & Components:**\n\t+ Gross Salary Components: Basic Salary, House Rent Allowance (HRA), Special Allowance, Performance Bonus, Leave Travel Allowance (LTA), and Medical Allowance.\n\t+ Taxability: Basic Salary, Special Allowance, and Performance Bonus are fully taxable, while HRA is partially exempt, and LTA is exempt subject to conditions.\n* **Payroll Calendar:**\n\t+ Payroll is processed on a monthly cycle with the following deadlines:\n\t\t- Attendance & Leave data freeze: 25th of the current month\n\t\t- Submission of payroll inputs: 26th of the current month\n\t\t- Payroll processing & computation: 27th-28th of the current month\n\t\t- Payroll review & approval: 29th of the current month\n\t\t- Salary disbursement: Last working day of the month\n\t\t- Payslip generation & distribution: Last working day of the month\n* **Attendance, Leave & Loss of Pay:**\n\t+ Attendance Integration: Payroll processing is directly integrated with the Company's attendance and leave management system (HRMS).\n\t+ Loss of Pay (LOP): Applied in cases of absence beyond available leave balance, uninformed or unapproved absence, absence during notice period, or suspension without pay.\n* **Expense Reimbursement:**\n\t+ Claims must be submitted with original supporting receipts/invoices within 30 days of incurring the expense.\n\t+ Reimbursements are tax-exempt only where substantiated by valid bills and within prescribed limits.\n* **Statutory Compliance & Deductions:**\n\t+ Artemis Technology Limited is committed to statutory compliance across all applicable jurisdictions.\n\t+ Statutory obligations include Employees' Provident Fund (EPF), Employee State Insurance (ESI), Professional Tax (PT), Tax Deducted at Source (TDS), Labour Welfare Fund (LWF), and Gratuity.\n* **Salary Revision & Increment Process:**\n\t+ Salary revisions are governed by the annual performance appraisal cycle and may also be triggered by promotions, market corrections, or role changes.\n\t+ Increment decisions are communicated by the HR team through official revision letters.\n* **Full & Final Settlement:**\n\t+ Upon separation from Artemis Technology Limited, the employee's Full & Final (F&F;) settlement will be processed in accordance with the Company's Separation & Exit Policy.\n\t+ The F&F; settlement shall include last month's salary, leave encashment, performance bonus (pro-rata), and gratuity.\n* **Record Retention:**\n\t+ Payroll records are maintained securely by the Finance and HR Divisions with restricted access.\n\t+ Records are subject to periodic audit by the Internal Audit and Compliance teams.\n* **Responsibilities:**\n\t+ Employees are responsible for ensuring their attendance and leave records are accurately updated in the HRMS system.\n\t+ Employees must raise a formal grievance through the designated payroll helpdesk email or HRMS ticketing portal within 7 working days of the salary credit date.\n* **Payroll Grievance Redressal:**\n\t+ The Payroll team will investigate the concern and provide a written response within 5 working days.\n\t+ If an error is found, the Payroll team will rectify it and notify the employee within 5 working days.\n\nSources:\n- Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n- Artemis_IT_Security_Policy (1).pdf	2026-04-14 09:49:48.239708
