211f5212-8ca1-4248-a733-f08bbbe2df4d	4d2a82e6-3abb-41c8-ba17-61bfed4c96a3	2	summarize payroll [policy	**Payroll Policy Summary**\n\n**Document:** Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n1. **Purpose:** The Payroll Policy establishes a comprehensive framework for accurate, timely, and compliant processing of employee compensation.\n2. **Scope:** The policy applies to all full-time and part-time employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees.\n3. **Guiding Principles:**\n\t* Accuracy & Timeliness: Payroll calculations and disbursements will be processed accurately and within the defined payroll calendar.\n\t* Confidentiality: Payroll information is strictly confidential and shall not be disclosed to unauthorized individuals.\n\t* Compliance: Artemis Technology Limited will adhere to applicable labour laws, tax regulations, and statutory obligations.\n\t* Transparency: Employees will receive itemized payslips detailing all earnings, deductions, and net pay.\n\t* Equity & Non-Discrimination: Payroll processes will be conducted in a fair and non-discriminatory manner.\n\t* Data Integrity: All payroll records will be maintained securely and accurately.\n4. **Payroll Timelines:**\n\t* Salary disbursement: 29th of the current month\n\t* Payslip generation & distribution: Last working day of the month\n\t* Statutory filing (PF, ESI, PT, TDS): 1st working day of the following month\n5. **Payroll Inputs:**\n\t* New joiner details, separation details, approved increment letters, attendance records, approved leave data, and loss-of-pay (LOP) details.\n\t* Approved overtime claims and shift allowance details (where applicable).\n6. **Mid-Month Salary (New Joiners & Separations):**\n\t* Salary will be computed on a pro-rata basis using the formula: (Monthly Gross Salary ÷ Number of Calendar Days in the Month) × Number of Days Worked.\n7. **Form 16 Issuance:**\n\t* Form 16 (Part A and Part B) will be issued to all employees by the 15th of June following the close of the financial year.\n8. **Payslips & Salary Statements:**\n\t* Monthly payslips will be issued electronically through the Company's HRMS portal by the 1st working day of the following month.\n\t* Each payslip will contain employee details, earnings breakdown, deductions, loss of pay (LOP) days, and net pay.\n9. **Payroll Confidentiality:**\n\t* Payroll data constitutes sensitive personal and financial information.\n\t* Employees, managers, HR personnel, and Finance staff are bound by confidentiality obligations.\n10. **Record Keeping:**\n\t* Monthly Payroll Register: Duration of employment + 8 years\n\t* Payslips (Employee Copies): Duration of employment + 8 years\n11. **Responsibilities:**\n\t* Employees: Submit accurate attendance, leave, investment declarations, and reimbursement claims on time.\n\t* Managers / Supervisors: Approve attendance, overtime, leaves, and reimbursements within stipulated timelines.\n\t* HR Business Partner: Submit payroll inputs, manage joiner/exit data, communicate policy to employees.\n\t* HR Operations / Payroll Team: Process payroll accurately and on schedule; distribute payslips; manage statutory filings.\n\t* Finance / Treasury: Approve payroll disbursement; manage statutory payments; maintain financial records.\n\t* Legal / Compliance: Ensure adherence to applicable labour and tax laws; advise on statutory changes.\n\t* CHRO & CFO: Final approval authority for payroll disbursement and policy deviations.\n12. **Payroll Grievance Redressal:**\n\t* Employees can raise a formal grievance through the following process:\n\t\t+ Step 1: Raise a Query with the HR Operations / Payroll team via the designated payroll helpdesk email or HRMS ticketing portal within 7 working days of the salary credit date.\n\t\t+ Step 2: Investigation & Resolution by the Payroll team within 5 working days.\n\t\t+ Step 3: Escalation to the HR Business Partner and subsequently to the HR Head for final resolution.\n\n**Employee Handbook Excerpt:**\n\n* Payroll: Salary or wage paid at the end of every month by bank transfers.\n* Performance Management: Quarterly performance reviews to ensure employees understand their job responsibilities, receive actionable feedback, and have opportunities for development and recognition.\n\nSources:\n- Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf	2026-04-13 16:07:49.339576
