y mentioned |\n\n**Key differences between Payroll Policy and Recruitment Policy (inferred):**\n\n* Focus: Payroll Policy focuses on payroll processing, disbursement, and confidentiality, while Recruitment Policy (inferred) focuses on the hiring process, job descriptions, and employee onboarding.\n* Scope: Payroll Policy has a specific scope and applies to all employees, contract employees, and interns, while Recruitment Policy (inferred) is focused on the recruitment process and does not have a specific scope.\n* Grievance redressal: Payroll Policy has a clear grievance redressal process, while Recruitment Policy (inferred) may have a grievance redressal process, but it is not explicitly mentioned.\n\nNote: The Recruitment Policy is not explicitly mentioned in the provided excerpts, so the comparison is based on inferences and general information about company policies and procedures.\n\nSources:\n- Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n- ArtemisDisciplinaryPolicy (2).pdf	2026-04-14 10:21:25.10511
