15551a0e-1557-4979-9709-b3c1186d03d9	102bc00a-b5c8-4ef1-ab11-968bdc7b7e30	3	leave policy	**Leave Policy Summary**\n\n**Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n* **Eligibility for Leave:**\n\t+ Eligible employees can continue their group health benefits for a limited period after leaving the company under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA).\n\t+ Covered spouses and children may also be able to extend their health coverage after certain qualifying events.\n* **Sick Leave:**\n\t+ Employees can take a partial day off or work from home if they are sick.\n\t+ Employees must inform their manager and send a sick leave request through the HRIS.\n\t+ Employees may be asked to submit a physician's note or other medical certification and/or complete a sick leave form if they are absent for more than three days.\n* **Long-term Illness:**\n\t+ The U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act provides employees 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period with the same group health benefits for medical and family reasons.\n\t+ Employees are eligible for this type of leave if they have worked for the company for more than 12 months and have worked at least 1,250 hours within 12 months before their leave begins.\n* **Bereavement Leave:**\n\t+ Employees are entitled to three days of paid bereavement leave to arrange a funeral or memorial service, attend a funeral or memorial service, resolve matters of inheritance, fulfill other family obligations, or mourn.\n\t+ Employees can take additional unpaid days off if they need to travel long-distance for a funeral or service.\n* **Jury Duty and Voting:**\n\t+ Exempt employees can take one day of unpaid leave extension of up to two months if they are called for jury duty.\n\t+ Non-exempt employees are entitled to paid jury duty leave according to national law.\n* **Parental Leave:**\n\t+ Employees are entitled to take parental leave to care for a new baby or adopted child.\n\t+ Employees must give at least three months' notice before their leave begins.\n\t+ Pregnant women can take part of their leave before labor if required by local or national law.\n\t+ Employees can ask for an unpaid leave extension of up to two months if they suffer complications during childbirth or have other issues.\n* **Returning to Work after Parental Leave:**\n\t+ The company offers remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms to help new parents transition back to work.\n* **Leaving the Company:**\n\t+ Employees can resign voluntarily by informing HR or their manager that they will stop working for the company.\n\t+ Employees are not obliged to give advance notice before resigning, but it is recommended for efficiency's sake.\n\t+ Employees who are laid off may receive references from their manager.\n\nSources:\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n### Other questions you would like to know about\n- Would you like to know more about Progressive Discipline Process?\n- Would you like to know more about Family and Medical Leave Act?\n- Would you like to know more about Jury Duty Leave Policy?	2026-04-16 10:56:08.081361
