2dc39047-eb98-42c1-8739-1e3e591b34e6	4b1ee7e5-f7e7-48f9-b6cd-7d78f8de84f8	2	paid leaves	**Paid Leaves Summary**\n\n**Policy Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n* **Paid Time Off (PTO):**\n\t+ Employees receive 20 days of PTO per year.\n\t+ PTO accrual begins on the day of joining the company and earns 1.7 days per month.\n\t+ Employees can take PTO at any time after the first week with the company.\n\t+ Additional PTO days are earned after the first year, with a cap at 25 days overall.\n\t+ Remaining PTO can be transferred to the next year.\n\t+ Accrued PTO may be compensated with the final paycheck upon leaving the company, according to local law.\n* **Holidays:**\n\t+ The company observes 12 federal holidays.\n\t+ A floating day can be taken as a holiday on any chosen day.\n\t+ Exempt employees are entitled to their normal compensation without deductions on holidays.\n\t+ Permanent non-exempt employees receive holiday pay after working for more than three months.\n* **Sick Leave:**\n\t+ Employees receive one week of paid sick leave.\n\t+ Sick leave can be taken for short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, and other indispositions.\n\t+ Employees with contagious diseases should use their sick days.\n* **Parental Leave:**\n\t+ The company offers support for new parents transitioning back to work after parental leave.\n\t+ Options include remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms.\n* **Jury Duty Leave:**\n\t+ Employees are entitled to paid jury duty leave according to national law.\n* **Bereavement Leave:**\n\t+ No specific information is provided in the policy excerpts.\n\n**Main Rules:**\n\n* Employees must request PTO through the HRIS system.\n* Managers or HR must approve PTO requests.\n* Employees do not need to specify a reason for requesting PTO.\n* Accrued PTO may be compensated with the final paycheck upon leaving the company, according to local law.\n\n**Critical Information:**\n\n* Employees should keep track of and report reimbursable expenses related to business travel, relocation, education, and training.\n* Employees should keep receipts for all reimbursable expenses and submit them to their manager within three months.\n* The company may compensate accrued vacation and sick leave upon termination, depending on local law.\n\nSources:\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n### Other questions you would like to know about\n- Would you like to know more about Severance Pay?\n- Would you like to know more about Returning to work after parental leave?\n- Would you like to know more about Paid Time Off (PTO)?	2026-04-16 15:40:38.618291
75284923-0094-4b53-9ca1-6760a66377b6	726b1929-fc7d-4ed4-a619-e96d379433ec	1	culture	**Artemis Employee Handbook: Culture**\n\n**Summary:**\n\nThe Artemis Employee Handbook outlines the company's culture, values, and expectations for employees. The following points summarize the key aspects of the company's culture:\n\n**Our Culture**\n\n* The way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver.\n* Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\n* Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge.\n* There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking.\n* Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\n\n**Our Vision**\n\n* The company's mission is to unlock organizational potential through tailored strategic insights and dependable client support.\n* The company sees itself as a long-term partner to its clients, not just a service provider.\n\n**Equal Opportunity Employment**\n\n* Artemis is an equal opportunity employer and does not tolerate discrimination against protected characteristics.\n* The company commits to penalizing every discriminatory, offensive, or inappropriate behavior.\n\n**Workplace Culture**\n\n* The company encourages employees to treat others with respect and professionalism.\n* Employees are expected to maintain professionalism and keep personal discussions outside of the workplace.\n* The company prohibits fraternization, including dating or being friends with colleagues, to avoid accusations of favoritism, abuse of authority, and sexual harassment.\n\n**Employee Relationships**\n\n* The company encourages friendships between peers, but expects employees to focus on their work and keep personal disputes outside of the workplace.\n* Employees are not allowed to date their managers or direct reports.\n\n**Conflicts of Interest**\n\n* Employees are expected to be vigilant to spot circumstances that create conflicts of interest, either to themselves or for their direct reports.\n* Employees are expected to follow the company's policies and always act in the company's best interests.\n\n**Employee Development**\n\n* The company encourages employees to share their ideas and suggestions for improving the workplace.\n* Employees are expected to maintain a high level of professionalism and adhere to the company's policies and procedures.\n\n**Acknowledgement**\n\n* Employees are required to sign an acknowledgement form to confirm that they have read and understood the employee handbook and are committed to following the company's policies.\n\nSources:\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n### Other questions you would like to know about\n- Would you like to know more about Conflict of Interest Policy?\n- Would you like to know more about Confidentiality and Data Protection Policy?\n- Would you like to know more about Workplace Harassment Policy?	2026-04-16 15:44:30.695107
95ea70a3-a3c3-4297-9eac-f9ca7734f209	e9df2ef2-7bb6-4049-8e14-30d0cf048f15	1	leave policy	Based on the provided policy excerpts, here are the relevant rules regarding leave policy:\n\n* If you are absent for more than three days of sick leave, you may need to provide a doctor's note and/or complete a sick leave form for insurance purposes. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)\n* Eligible employees have access to an insurance package. For more information, contact HR. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)\n* According to the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA), eligible employees may choose to continue their group health benefits for a limited period after leaving the company due to a qualifying event, such as termination for reasons other than gross misconduct and reduction in hours of employment. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)	2026-04-16 10:17:42.596127
6d79f4fc-d118-4dce-8e00-829d60cf344d	e9df2ef2-7bb6-4049-8e14-30d0cf048f15	2	what is leave policy	**Leave Policy Summary**\n\n**Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n* **Sick Leave:**\n\t+ Inform manager and send a sick leave request through HRIS if you become sick.\n\t+ Take a partial day off or work from home, but rest and recuperate for a day before returning to work.\n\t+ Use PTO or arrange for a flexible work schedule for routine health care appointments.\n\t+ Submit a physician's note or other medical certification and/or complete a sick leave form for absences over three days.\n* **Long-term Illness (Family and Medical Leave Act):**\n\t+ 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period for medical and family reasons.\n\t+ Eligible for leave if you have worked for over 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before leave begins.\n* **Bereavement Leave:**\n\t+ Up to two months of unpaid leave extension for bereavement.\n\t+ Contact HR as soon as possible to arrange this.\n* **Parental Leave:**\n\t+ Eligible for leave if you have worked for over 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before leave begins.\n\t+ Three months' notice before leave begins is recommended.\n\t+ Up to two months of unpaid leave extension for complications during childbirth or other issues.\n* **PTO (Paid Time Off):**\n\t+ You can transfer any remaining PTO to the next year.\n\t+ We encourage you to use your time off throughout the year.\n\t+ Accrued PTO may be compensated with your final paycheck according to local law.\n\n**Main Rules:**\n\n* Provide advance notice for resignation, ideally two weeks or a month for highly specialized or executive positions.\n* Submit a written and signed resignation letter.\n* You are not obliged to give advance notice before resigning, but it is recommended for efficiency's sake.\n\n**Critical Information:**\n\n* If you are laid off, you may receive references from your manager.\n* If you resign, you may ask for references, and your manager has the right to oblige or refuse.\n\nSources:\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\n\n### Other questions you would like to know about\n- Would you like to know more about Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA)?\n- Would you like to know more about Progressive Discipline Process?\n- Would you like to know more about PTO (Paid Time Off) Policy?	2026-04-16 15:47:54.219375
