bc9f0ea1-e8e2-4879-a871-2cd564d541fa	\N	what are the employee policies?	Based on the provided policy excerpts, the following employee policies are mentioned. Employee Handbook. This policy is a comprehensive guide for employees, contractors, volunteers, vendors, and stakeholders. It outlines the company's expectations and policies for building a productive, lawful, and pleasant workplace. (. Confidentiality and Data Protection. This policy ensures that private information about clients, employees, partners, and the company is well. Protected. Examples of confidential information include employee records, unpublished financial information, customer data, and unpublished goals and initiatives. (. Non. Compete and Non. Disclosure Agreements (NDAs). As part of the hiring process, employees may be asked to sign NDAs to protect confidential information. Code of Conduct & Ethics Policy. This policy is related to the Disciplinary Policy and outlines the company's expectations for employee behavior and conduct. (. Anti. Harassment & POSH Policy. This policy is related to the Disciplinary Policy and outlines the company's expectations for preventing harassment and promoting a positive work environment. (. Grievance Redressal Policy. This policy is related to the Disciplinary Policy and outlines the process for addressing employee grievances. (. Compensation & Benefits Policy. This policy outlines the company's compensation and benefits structure, including salary disbursement, statutory deductions, reimbursements, and overtime. (. Leave Policy. This policy outlines the company's leave policies, including paid time off, sick leave, and vacation time. (. Expense Reimbursement & Travel Policy. This policy outlines the company's policies for expense reimbursement and travel, including procedures for submitting expense reports and claiming reimbursement. (. Separation & Exit Policy. This policy outlines the company's procedures for employee separation and exit, including notice periods, final settlements, and post. Employment obligations. (. Data Privacy & Confidentiality Policy. This policy outlines the company's expectations for protecting confidential information and ensuring data privacy. (. IT & Acceptable Use Policy. This policy outlines the company's expectations for employee use of IT systems and resources, including email, internet, and software usage. (. Disciplinary Policy. This policy outlines the company's procedures for addressing employee misconduct, including disciplinary actions and appeals. (. Whistleblower Policy. This policy outlines the company's procedures for reporting and addressing whistleblower complaints, including confidentiality and protection for whistleblowers. (. These policies are subject to periodic review and update, and employees are encouraged to contact HR or designated helpdesks for any clarifications or questions.	2026-04-13 04:36:32.058059
