f0f691a8-6c95-4edc-aa15-f4358e8fc2e2	\N	what is the leave policy	Based on the provided policy excerpts, the leave policy is as follows. Leave Policy Overview. The leave policy is outlined in the Artemis Employee Handbook. The policy aims to provide employees with a fair and equal opportunity to take leave for various reasons, including medical, family, and other reasons. Types of Leave. Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA). Eligible employees who have worked for the company for more than 12 months are entitled to 12 weeks of unpaid, job. Protected leave in a 12. Month period for medical and family reasons, including. Recovering from a serious health condition. Caring for an immediate family member with a serious health condition. Pregnancy Leave. Pregnant women can take part of their leave before labor, depending on local or national law. Maternity Leave. New mothers are required to give at least three months' notice before their leave begins. Long. Term Illness. The company will follow the U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act for employees with long. Term illnesses. Other Leave. The company may provide other types of leave, such as non. Smoking and substance abuse policies, to protect employee health. Procedures and Deadlines. Notice Period. Employees are required to give at least three months' notice before their leave begins. Leave Application. Employees should contact HR to arrange their leave. Qualifying Events. Employees may be eligible for COBRA benefits after a qualifying event, such as termination for reasons other than gross misconduct and reduction in hours of employment. Related Policies. The leave policy is related to the following policies. Employee Handbook. Compensation & Benefits Policy. Expense Reimbursement & Travel Policy. Separation & Exit Policy. Data Privacy & Confidentiality Policy. Acknowledgment. By continuing employment at Artemis Technology Limited, all employees are deemed to have read, understood, and agreed to abide by the terms of the leave policy. Employees are encouraged to contact the HR Division for any clarifications.	2026-04-13 05:29:11.795344
