ca7820a2-9906-41b3-bf0b-f4b86adf7dbc	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	document_summarization	{"query": "what is leave policy?", "user_role": "employee", "selected_tool": "document_summarization"}	{"sources": [{"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "page_number": null}], "summary": "**Leave Policy Summary**\\n\\n**Source:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Eligibility:**\\n\\n* Eligible employees are entitled to various types of leave, including:\\n\\t+ Sick leave\\n\\t+ Paid time off (PTO)\\n\\t+ Holidays\\n\\t+ Bereavement leave\\n\\t+ Parental leave\\n\\t+ Long-term illness (up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave)\\n\\t+ Jury duty and voting\\n\\t+ Paternity and maternity leave\\n\\n**Leave Types:**\\n\\n* **Sick Leave:**\\n\\t+ Use sick days for flu or other contagious diseases\\n\\t+ Inform manager and send sick leave request through HRIS\\n\\t+ May take partial day off or work from home\\n\\t+ Rest and recuperate for a day before returning to work\\n* **Paid Time Off (PTO):**\\n\\t+ Use for routine healthcare (e.g. doctor's/dentist's appointments)\\n\\t+ Arrange for flexible work schedule if needed\\n* **Bereavement Leave:**\\n\\t+ Up to 2 months of unpaid leave extension\\n\\t+ Contact HR to arrange\\n* **Parental Leave:**\\n\\t+ Offered to new parents\\n\\t+ Includes remote working/flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms\\n* **Long-term Illness:**\\n\\t+ Up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave\\n\\t+ Eligible employees must have worked for 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months\\n* **Jury Duty and Voting:**\\n\\t+ Eligible employees may take time off for jury duty and voting\\n* **Paternity and Maternity Leave:**\\n\\t+ Eligible employees may take time off for paternity and maternity leave\\n\\n**Exceptions:**\\n\\n* None mentioned in the provided policy content\\n\\n**Approval Flow:**\\n\\n* Sick leave: inform manager and send sick leave request through HRIS\\n* Bereavement leave: contact HR to arrange\\n* Parental leave: contact HR for more information\\n* Long-term illness: contact HR for more information\\n* Jury duty and voting: no approval required\\n* Paternity and maternity leave: no approval required\\n\\n**Important Numbers and Dates:**\\n\\n* 12 weeks: maximum leave duration for long-term illness\\n* 1,250 hours: minimum hours required within 12 months for long-term illness eligibility\\n* 2 months: maximum bereavement leave extension\\n* 3 consecutive days: minimum notice required for resignation\\n* 2 weeks: minimum notice required for resignation (for most employees)\\n* 1 month: minimum notice required for resignation (for highly specialized or executive positions)", "chunks_used": 10, "summary_type": "concise"}	2026-04-10 12:50:14.221757
453abca1-80d6-4841-be37-042d74f0b617	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	policy_retrieval	{"query": "what is the culture at artemis?", "user_role": "employee", "selected_tool": "policy_retrieval"}	{"answer": "• Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\\n• Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge.\\n• There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking.\\n• Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n \\n[Source: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, page None, line 6]", "sources": [{"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 6, "line_number": 7, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 5, "line_number": 6, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 3, "line_number": 4, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 4, "line_number": 5, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 8, "line_number": 9, "page_number": null}], "retrieved_chunks": [{"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "work is recognized through impact rather than visibility. \\nOur Vision \\nOur mission is to unlock organizational potential through tailored strategic insights and \\ndependable client support. In practice, this means helping organizations move from \\nuncertainty to direction, and from direction to measurable progress. \\nWe see Artemis as a long-term partner to our clients, not just a service provider. The", "chunk_index": 6, "line_number": 7, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "approach remains consistent—listen carefully, think rigorously, and follow through with \\ndependable support. \\nOur Culture \\nAt Artemis, the way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver. Teams are \\nencouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their \\ncontributions. Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to \\nbring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge. \\nThere is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking. Whether \\ndrafting a report or leading a client discussion, employees are expected to make their \\nideas understandable and actionable. Titles matter less than accountability, and good \\nwork is recognized through impact rather than visibility. \\nOur Vision", "chunk_index": 5, "line_number": 6, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "Welcome \\nHello and welcome! Thank you for joining Artemis, where we strive to unlock organizational \\npotential through tailored strategic insights and unparalleled client support. We can’t wait to see \\nwhat you will achieve with us. \\nThis employee handbook defines who we are and how we work together. We will do \\neverything possible to create a fair and productive workplace, but we need your help. \\nWe’ve created this handbook to guide you. \\nThis handbook isn’t a contract or a guarantee of employment. It’s a collection of our \\nexpectations, commitments and responsibilities. Please read this employee handbook \\ncarefully and consult it whenever you need to. \\n \\nGetting to know our company \\nArtemis was founded with a simple observation: many organizations struggle not", "chunk_index": 3, "line_number": 4, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "Getting to know our company \\nArtemis was founded with a simple observation: many organizations struggle not \\nbecause they lack ambition, but because they lack clarity. In its early days, the \\ncompany operated as a small advisory group, working closely with a handful of clients \\nto untangle operational challenges and provide structured direction. What began as a \\nfocused effort to support decision-making has grown into a broader enterprise \\ndedicated to helping organizations better understand themselves and act with intention. \\nToday, Artemis works across industries, supporting leaders in translating complex \\nsituations into practical strategies. While the scope of our work has expanded, the \\napproach remains consistent—listen carefully, think rigorously, and follow through with", "chunk_index": 4, "line_number": 5, "page_number": null}, {"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "company’s full benefits package. \\n \\nWe remind you that, in the U.S., employment is “at-will.” This means that you or our \\ncompany may terminate our employment relationship at any time and for any non-\\ndiscriminatory reason(s). \\n \\nEqual opportunity employment \\nArtemis is an equal opportunity employer. We don’t tolerate discrimination against \\nprotected characteristics (gender, age, sexual orientation, race, nationality, ethnicity, \\nreligion, disability, veteran status.) We want all employees (including executives and \\nHR) to treat others with respect and professionalism. In practice, this means that we: \\n \\n■ [Hire and promote people based on skills, experience or potential and try to \\nreduce bias in every process (e.g. through structured interviews.)]", "chunk_index": 8, "line_number": 9, "page_number": null}]}	2026-04-10 13:02:45.977351
5190d67b-3436-43ac-994c-11739eec01bc	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	document_summarization	{"query": "what is culture at artemis?", "user_role": "employee", "selected_tool": "document_summarization"}	{"sources": [{"category": "general", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "page_number": null}], "summary": "**Summary of Culture at Artemis**\\n\\n**Culture Overview:**\\nAt Artemis, the way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver. Our culture is built on collaboration, clarity, and accountability.\\n\\n**Key Principles:**\\n\\n* **Collaboration:** Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\\n* **Clarity:** There is a strong emphasis on clear communication and thinking.\\n* **Accountability:** Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n\\n**Eligibility:** All employees are expected to adhere to these principles.\\n\\n**Exceptions:** None mentioned.\\n\\n**Approval Flow:** Not applicable.\\n\\n**Source Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Additional Notes:**\\n\\n* Artemis is an equal opportunity employer and does not tolerate discrimination against protected characteristics.\\n* The company is a smoke-free and drug-free workplace.\\n* Employees are expected to behave professionally and avoid conflicts of interest.\\n* Fraternization (dating or being friends with colleagues) is subject to guidelines and expectations.", "chunks_used": 10, "summary_type": "concise"}	2026-04-10 13:04:22.640534
