1cad80f9-3bc0-4108-b9dd-face9c3beb36	a43f2bcc-78f3-41c0-8169-3bc49031bc7e	summarization_tool	{"query": "summarize payroll policy", "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "**Payroll Policy Summary**\\n\\n**Document:** Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n1. **Purpose:** The Payroll Policy establishes a comprehensive framework for accurate, timely, and compliant processing of employee compensation.\\n2. **Scope:** The policy applies to all full-time and part-time employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees.\\n3. **Guiding Principles:**\\n\\t* Accuracy & Timeliness: Payroll calculations and disbursements will be processed accurately and within the defined payroll calendar.\\n\\t* Confidentiality: Payroll information is strictly confidential and will not be disclosed to unauthorized individuals.\\n\\t* Compliance: Artemis Technology Limited will adhere to applicable labour laws, tax regulations, and statutory obligations.\\n\\t* Transparency: Employees will receive itemized payslips detailing all earnings, deductions, and net pay.\\n\\t* Equity & Non-Discrimination: Payroll processes will be conducted in a fair and non-discriminatory manner.\\n\\t* Data Integrity: All payroll records will be maintained securely and accurately.\\n4. **Payroll Timelines:**\\n\\t* Salary disbursement: 29th of the current month\\n\\t* Payslip generation & distribution: Last working day of the month\\n\\t* Statutory filing (PF, ESI, PT, TDS): 1st working day of the following month\\n5. **Payroll Inputs:**\\n\\t* New joiner details\\n\\t* Separation details\\n\\t* Approved increment letters or salary revision notifications\\n\\t* Attendance records\\n\\t* Approved overtime claims and shift allowance details\\n6. **Statutory Compliance & Deductions:**\\n\\t* Employees' Provident Fund (EPF)\\n\\t* Employee State Insurance (ESI)\\n\\t* Professional Tax (PT)\\n\\t* Tax Deducted at Source (TDS)\\n\\t* Labour Welfare Fund (LWF)\\n\\t* Gratuity (Accrual & Payment)\\n7. **Payroll Confidentiality:**\\n\\t* Payroll data constitutes sensitive personal and financial information.\\n\\t* Employees, managers, HR personnel, and Finance staff are bound by confidentiality obligations.\\n8. **Record Keeping:**\\n\\t* Monthly Payroll Register: Duration of employment + 8 years\\n\\t* Payslips (Employee Copies): Duration of employment + 8 years\\n9. **Responsibilities:**\\n\\t* Employee: Submit accurate attendance, leave, investment declarations, and reimbursement claims on time.\\n\\t* Manager/Supervisor: Approve attendance, overtime, leaves, and reimbursements within stipulated timelines.\\n\\t* HR Business Partner: Submit payroll inputs, manage joiner/exit data, communicate policy to employees.\\n\\t* HR Operations/Payroll Team: Process payroll accurately and on schedule; distribute payslips; manage statutory filings.\\n\\t* Finance/Treasury: Approve payroll disbursement; manage statutory payments; maintain financial records.\\n\\t* Legal/Compliance: Ensure adherence to applicable labour and tax laws; advise on statutory changes.\\n10. **Payroll Grievance Redressal:**\\n\\t* Employees can raise a formal grievance through the following process:\\n\\t\\t1. Raise a Query\\n\\t\\t2. Investigation & Resolution\\n\\t\\t3. Escalation (if not satisfied with the resolution)\\n\\n**Related Policy:** Employee Handbook (Section: Payroll)", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 2}	2026-04-16 06:49:13.46838
a6d2f78f-f64a-4ab5-b8b6-59ba7b9cbdda	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	document_summarization	{"query": "what are the benefits at artemis?", "user_role": "employee", "selected_tool": "document_summarization"}	{"sources": [{"category": "leave", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "page_number": null}], "summary": "**Summary of Benefits at Artemis**\\n\\nBased on the Artemis Payroll Policy (HR-PP-002) and the Employee Handbook, the benefits at Artemis include:\\n\\n**Eligibility:**\\n\\n* All full-time and part-time employees of Artemis Technology Limited\\n* Contract employees and consultants remunerated through the Company's payroll system\\n* Interns and trainees receiving stipends under Artemis supervision\\n\\n**Benefits:**\\n\\n* **Salary Structure:**\\n + Basic Salary (fully taxable)\\n + House Rent Allowance (HRA) (partially exempt)\\n + Special Allowance (fully taxable)\\n + Performance Bonus (fully taxable)\\n + Leave Travel Allowance (LTA) (exempt, subject to conditions)\\n + Medical Allowance (exempt)\\n* **Other Benefits:**\\n + Overtime pay\\n + Reimbursements\\n + Advances\\n + Final settlements\\n\\n**Exceptions:**\\n\\n* Not specified in the provided policy content\\n\\n**Approval Flow:**\\n\\n* Not specified in the provided policy content\\n\\n**Source Documents:**\\n\\n* Artemis Payroll Policy (HR-PP-002)\\n* Artemis Employee Handbook\\n\\n**Effective Date:**\\n\\n* April 2025\\n\\n**Version:**\\n\\n* 1.0", "chunks_used": 10, "summary_type": "concise"}	2026-04-10 15:03:40.62967
7f2aac00-ffe3-4563-9805-1efea88dbc82	5cc9ad7c-a73c-46b8-a2ac-49c57117ec74	policy_retrieval	{"query": "what is the dress code at artemis?", "user_role": "employee", "selected_tool": "policy_retrieval"}	{"answer": "Our company’s official dress code is Business Casual. However, an employee’s position may also inform how they should dress. If you frequently meet with clients or prospects, conform to a more formal dress code. We expect you to be clean when coming to work and avoid wearing clothes that are unprofessional (e.g. workout clothes.) \\nAs long as you conform with our guidelines above, we don’t have specific expectations about what types of clothes or accessories you should wear. \\nWe also respect and permit grooming styles, clothing and accessories that are dictated by religious beliefs, ethnicity or disability. \\n(Source: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, page None, line 35)", "sources": [{"category": "leave", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 34, "line_number": 35, "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "chunk_index": 0, "line_number": 1, "page_number": null}, {"category": "leave", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_index": 3, "line_number": 4, "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "chunk_index": 46, "line_number": 47, "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "chunk_index": 33, "line_number": 34, "page_number": null}], "retrieved_chunks": [{"category": "leave", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "Dress code \\nOur company’s official dress code is Business Casual. However, an employee’s \\nposition may also inform how they should dress. If you frequently meet with clients or \\nprospects, conform to a more formal dress code. We expect you to be clean when \\ncoming to work and avoid wearing clothes that are unprofessional (e.g. workout \\nclothes.) \\nAs long as you conform with our guidelines above, we don’t have specific expectations \\nabout what types of clothes or accessories you should wear. \\n \\nWe also respect and permit grooming styles, clothing and accessories that are dictated \\nby religious beliefs, ethnicity or disability. \\n \\nCyber security and digital devices \\nThis section deals with all things digital at work. We want to set some guidelines for", "chunk_index": 34, "line_number": 35, "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "chunk_text": "ARTEMIS TECHNOLOGY LIMITED\\n PAYROLL POLICY\\n Human Resources Division\\nPolicy Code\\nHR-PP-002\\nVersion\\n1.0\\nEffective Date\\nApril 2025\\nLast Reviewed\\nApril 2025\\nApproved By\\nChief Human Resources Officer, Artemis Technology\\nLimited\\nClassification\\nConfidential — Internal Use Only", "chunk_index": 0, "line_number": 1, "page_number": null}, {"category": "leave", "file_name": "artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunk_text": "Welcome \\nHello and welcome! Thank you for joining Artemis, where we strive to unlock organizational \\npotential through tailored strategic insights and unparalleled client support. We can’t wait to see \\nwhat you will achieve with us. \\nThis employee handbook defines who we are and how we work together. We will do \\neverything possible to create a fair and productive workplace, but we need your help. \\nWe’ve created this handbook to guide you. \\nThis handbook isn’t a contract or a guarantee of employment. It’s a collection of our \\nexpectations, commitments and responsibilities. Please read this employee handbook \\ncarefully and consult it whenever you need to. \\n \\nGetting to know our company \\nArtemis was founded with a simple observation: many organizations struggle not", "chunk_index": 3, "line_number": 4, "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "chunk_text": "PAYROLL POLICY\\nArtemis Technology Limited  |  HR-PP-002\\nConfidential — For Internal Use Only  |  Human Resources Division, Artemis Technology Limited\\nPage 12\\n Artemis Technology Limited — Human Resources Division | Policy Code: HR-PP-002 | Version 1.0 | Effective April 2025", "chunk_index": 46, "line_number": 47, "page_number": null}, {"category": "payroll", "file_name": "Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf", "chunk_text": "PAYROLL POLICY\\nArtemis Technology Limited  |  HR-PP-002\\nConfidential — For Internal Use Only  |  Human Resources Division, Artemis Technology Limited\\nPage 12\\n Artemis Technology Limited — Human Resources Division | Policy Code: HR-PP-002 | Version 1.0 | Effective April 2025", "chunk_index": 33, "line_number": 34, "page_number": null}]}	2026-04-10 15:06:12.116899
92dd8060-1e2a-48a0-b87e-a7ad937bb08c	5f9b140e-1be2-4eb6-91fc-d33f9df5f798	recommendation_tool	{"query": "payroll policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided document excerpts, here are some relevant policy topics related to the user's query 'payroll policy':\\n\\n* **Payroll Schedule**: This policy outlines the frequency and timing of payroll payments, as mentioned in the excerpt \\"We pay your salary or wage at the end of every month by bank transfers.\\"\\n* **Compensation Status**: This policy explains the compensation structure, including hourly rates, premium pay for holidays, and additional PTO for exempt employees, as mentioned in the excerpt \\"If you are a non-exempt employee, you will receive your regular hourly rate with a premium for working on a holiday.\\"\\n* **Overtime Policy**: This policy governs the payment of overtime, as mentioned in the excerpt \\"If you are a non-exempt employee, you will receive your regular hourly rate with a premium for working on a holiday.\\"\\n* **PTO Accrual and Usage**: This policy outlines the rules for accruing and using Paid Time Off (PTO), as mentioned in the excerpt \\"Employees receive [20 days] of Paid Time Off (PTO) per year.\\"\\n* **Payroll Tax and Benefits**: This policy explains the company's policies on payroll taxes, benefits, and deductions, although it is not explicitly mentioned in the provided excerpts.\\n* **Payroll Dispute Resolution**: This policy outlines the procedures for resolving disputes related to payroll, although it is not explicitly mentioned in the provided excerpts.\\n\\nThese policy topics are relevant to the user's query 'payroll policy' and can be found in the provided document excerpts.", "chunks_count": 15, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 04:02:30.464648
af85ab8c-0ce6-4839-bfc1-9206edb817fa	111a6a4b-5853-4593-a68c-9b67527a18d7	comparison_tool	{"query": "culture and dress code", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Culture and Dress Code Policies**\\n\\n**Policy Documents:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Comparison Focus:** Culture and Dress Code\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n| Policy | Culture | Dress Code |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Mutual Respect | Our workplace is founded on mutual respect and we won’t allow anyone to compromise this foundation. |  |\\n| Professionalism | We want to ensure that relationships between employees are appropriate and harmonious. We outline our guidelines and we ask you to always behave professionally. |  |\\n| Cleanliness | We expect you to be clean when coming to work and avoid wearing clothes that are unprofessional (e.g. workout clothes.) |  |\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| Policy | Culture | Dress Code |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Work Environment | At Artemis, the way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver. Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions. | Our company’s official dress code is Business Casual. However, an employee’s position may also inform how they should dress. |\\n| Communication | There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking. Whether drafting a report or leading a client discussion, employees are expected to make their ideas understandable and actionable. | As long as you conform with our guidelines above, we don’t have specific expectations about what types of clothes or accessories you should wear. |\\n| Adaptability | Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge. |  |\\n| Recognition | Good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility. |  |\\n| Formality | If you frequently meet with clients or prospects, conform to a more formal dress code. |  |\\n| Accommodations | We respect and permit grooming styles, clothing and accessories that are dictated by religious beliefs, ethnicity or disability. |  |\\n| Social Media | If you handle our social media accounts or speak on our company’s behalf, we expect you to protect our company’s image and reputation. |  |\\n\\n**Key Takeaways:**\\n\\n* Artemis values a culture of mutual respect, professionalism, and cleanliness.\\n* The dress code is Business Casual, but employees are expected to adapt to more formal dress codes when meeting with clients or prospects.\\n* Employees are encouraged to be adaptable, communicate clearly, and recognize good work through impact rather than visibility.\\n* The company respects and accommodates employees with different grooming styles, clothing, and accessories due to religious beliefs, ethnicity, or disability.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 04:31:49.605398
26b55cae-5b4e-45b3-9302-3d9203b6caf2	63dfb4c4-3725-48c2-b8a4-8df22614990a	summarization_tool	{"query": "culture at artemis", "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "**Culture at Artemis**\\n\\nBased on the provided policy excerpts, here is a summary of the culture at Artemis:\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n* **Collaboration**: Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions. Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic.\\n* **Clarity**: There is a strong emphasis on clarity in communication and thinking. Employees are expected to make their ideas understandable and actionable.\\n* **Accountability**: Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n* **Long-term partnership**: Artemis sees itself as a long-term partner to its clients, not just a service provider.\\n\\n**Main Rules:**\\n\\n* Employees are expected to work together, share ideas, and take ownership of their contributions.\\n* Clarity in communication and thinking is essential for effective collaboration.\\n* Accountability is valued over titles or visibility.\\n\\n**Critical Information:**\\n\\n* Artemis's culture is built on the principles of collaboration, clarity, and accountability.\\n* The company prioritizes long-term partnerships with its clients.\\n\\n**Policy Documents:**\\n\\n* Employee Handbook (artemis_employee_handbook.pdf)\\n* Artemis's Culture section (Getting to know our company and Our Culture)", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-16 14:19:26.149887
