ec5917a3-6386-453e-91f6-c764ed1cb3a6	fa9b4cd2-9883-403d-9a37-b62717f0dce8	comparison_tool	{"query": "paid time off and sick leave", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Paid Time Off (PTO) and Sick Leave Policies**\\n\\n**Policy Documents:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Comparison Focus:** Paid Time Off (PTO) and Sick Leave\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n| Feature | PTO | Sick Leave |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Accrual begins | Day of joining the company | N/A |\\n| Accrual rate | 1.7 days per month | N/A |\\n| Maximum accrual | 25 days overall | N/A |\\n| Transfer to next year | Yes | N/A |\\n| Compensation upon termination | May be compensated according to local law | May be compensated according to local law |\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| Feature | PTO | Sick Leave |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Accrual amount | 20 days per year | 1 week (varies by state/country) |\\n| Eligibility | All employees | All employees |\\n| Reason for taking leave | Any reason | Short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, etc. |\\n| Request process | Send request through HRIS | Send sick leave request through HRIS |\\n| Approval process | Manager or HR approval | Manager approval |\\n| Use of PTO | Can use PTO for sick leave | Can use PTO for routine health care appointments |\\n| Certification requirements | May require physician's note or medical certification | May require physician's note or medical certification |\\n| Long-term illness | Not addressed | Addressed through FMLA and company policy |\\n| Paternity and maternity leave | Not addressed | Addressed through FMLA and company policy |\\n\\n**Key Takeaways:**\\n\\n* PTO and sick leave have different accrual amounts and eligibility requirements.\\n* PTO can be used for any reason, while sick leave is only for short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, etc.\\n* Both PTO and sick leave have similar compensation and transfer policies upon termination.\\n* Long-term illness and paternity/maternity leave are addressed through FMLA and company policy.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-14 04:19:13.262846
