b63261ab-0cc9-4cf8-a5cc-bf470e731ad2	703d436f-2f92-4f07-bb76-40ae55895b31	comparison_tool	{"query": "compare between paid and unpaid leaves", "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Paid and Unpaid Leaves between artemis_employee_handbook.pdf and Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf**\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n* Both documents mention the importance of keeping accurate attendance and leave records.\\n* Both documents require employees to submit claims with supporting documentation for reimbursement.\\n* Both documents have a time limit for submitting claims (30 days in Artemis_Payroll_Policy and not specified in artemis_employee_handbook.pdf).\\n* Both documents mention the importance of pre-approval for leave and reimbursement.\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| **Category** | **Artemis_Employee_Handbook.pdf** | **Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf** |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| **Paid Time Off (PTO)** | Employees receive 20 days of PTO per year, with an additional day per year after the first year. | Not mentioned |\\n| **Sick Leave** | Employees receive 1 week of paid sick leave, with additional days in states or countries with more generous laws. | Not mentioned |\\n| **Unpaid Leave Extension** | Employees can take an unpaid leave extension of up to 2 months, with prior approval from HR. | Not mentioned |\\n| **Leave Encashment** | Not mentioned | Employees are entitled to encashment of unused Earned Leave (EL) balance upon separation. |\\n| **Gratuity** | Not mentioned | Employees are entitled to gratuity upon completion of 5 years of continuous service. |\\n| **Notice Period** | Employees are required to give at least a month's notice, when possible, for parental leave. | Not mentioned |\\n| **Parental Leave** | Employees are entitled to parental leave, with options for remote working, flexible hours, and onsite/external paid daycare. | Not mentioned |\\n| **Termination** | Employees may be terminated for cause or without cause, with severance pay and assistance in finding new employment. | Not mentioned |\\n\\n**Key Differences:**\\n\\n* Artemis_Employee_Handbook.pdf provides more detailed information on paid time off, sick leave, and parental leave, while Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf focuses on attendance, leave, and loss of pay.\\n* Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf provides more detailed information on leave encashment, gratuity, and termination procedures.\\n* Artemis_Employee_Handbook.pdf emphasizes the importance of pre-approval for leave and reimbursement, while Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf requires pre-approval for reimbursement and has a specific time limit for submitting claims.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 2}	2026-04-14 04:38:42.230156
