05d344dd-72eb-4b2c-ae6a-dd7f41d835d1	703d436f-2f92-4f07-bb76-40ae55895b31	comparison_tool	{"query": "compare between investigation and code of conduct", "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "**Comparison between Investigation and Code of Conduct**\\n\\nBased on the provided policy excerpts, here are the differences and similarities between Investigation and Code of Conduct:\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n| **Category** | **Investigation** | **Code of Conduct** |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| **Purpose** | To address employee conduct and performance issues | To establish a fair and transparent framework for addressing employee conduct and performance issues |\\n| **Objective** | To encourage positive behavioral change and maintain a respectful and productive work environment | To encourage positive behavioral change and maintain a respectful and productive work environment |\\n| **Disciplinary Process** | Progressive disciplinary process with six stages of increasing severity | Progressive discipline process with six steps of increasing severity |\\n| **Termination** | Termination may be immediate and without prior warnings for gross misconduct | Termination may be immediate and without prior warnings for gross misconduct |\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| **Category** | **Investigation** | **Code of Conduct** |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| **Initiation** | Initiated when a complaint is filed, a manager escalates an incident, or HR identifies a potential breach of policy | Not explicitly stated |\\n| **Investigating Officer** | Appointed by HR, typically a senior HR professional or a neutral department head | Not explicitly stated |\\n| **Notification** | Employee under investigation will be formally notified in writing of the nature of the allegation, commencement of the investigation, and their rights during the process | Not explicitly stated |\\n| **Evidence Gathering** | IO will gather relevant evidence including documents, emails, CCTV footage, system logs, and witness statements | Not explicitly stated |\\n| **Employee Interview** | Employee will be given a formal opportunity to respond to the allegations | Not explicitly stated |\\n| **Investigation Report** | IO will prepare a report detailing the findings and recommendations | Not explicitly stated |\\n| **Roles and Responsibilities** | Clearly defined roles and responsibilities for managers, HR, and Legal/Compliance | Not explicitly stated |\\n\\n**Investigation Specifics:**\\n\\n* Initiated when a complaint is filed, a manager escalates an incident, or HR identifies a potential breach of policy\\n* Appointed Investigating Officer (IO) by HR\\n* Formal notification to employee under investigation\\n* Gathering of evidence and employee interview\\n* Preparation of investigation report\\n\\n**Code of Conduct Specifics:**\\n\\n* Establishes a fair and transparent framework for addressing employee conduct and performance issues\\n* Progressive discipline process with six steps of increasing severity\\n* Termination may be immediate and without prior warnings for gross misconduct\\n* Employee Code of Conduct outlines additional expectations for employee behavior at work", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 3}	2026-04-14 04:39:56.672823
