812d87c2-ac03-4adb-9f5f-44858f8c1eb9	34aef272-e6a7-4ba9-8041-17137ad814da	comparison_tool	{"query": "what is leave policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Leave Policies in artemis_employee_handbook.pdf**\\n\\n**Leave Policy Comparison Table:**\\n\\n| **Leave Type** | **Similarities** | **Differences** |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| **Sick Leave** | Employees can take a partial day off or work from home, and must inform their manager and send a sick leave request through HRIS. | No specific duration for sick leave is mentioned, but a physician's note or medical certification may be required for absences exceeding 3 days. |\\n| **Family and Medical Leave (FMLA)** | Eligible employees can take up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period for medical and family reasons. | Employees must have worked for the company for more than 12 months and have worked at least 1,250 hours within 12 months before their leave begins. |\\n| **Bereavement Leave** | Employees can take an unpaid leave extension of up to 2 months to cope and mourn after losing a loved one. | No specific duration for bereavement leave is mentioned, but employees should contact HR as soon as possible to arrange this. |\\n| **Parental Leave** | New parents can take leave and return to work with support from the company, including remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid daycare, and lactation rooms. | Employees should give at least 3 months' notice before their leave begins, and may be eligible for an unpaid leave extension of up to 2 months if they suffer complications during childbirth or have other issues. |\\n| **PTO (Paid Time Off)** | Employees can use PTO for routine healthcare appointments, and can transfer any remaining PTO to the next year. | Employees may be compensated for accrued PTO with their final paycheck according to local law, and can use PTO or arrange for a flexible work schedule for routine healthcare appointments. |\\n| **Jury Duty Leave** | Employees may be entitled to paid jury duty leave according to national law. | No specific duration for jury duty leave is mentioned, but the company will follow national law. |\\n| **Pregnancy Leave** | Pregnant women may be eligible for part of their leave before labor, and can take an unpaid leave extension of up to 2 months if they suffer complications during childbirth or have other issues. | Employees should give at least 3 months' notice before their leave begins, and may be eligible for onsite/external paid daycare and lactation rooms. |\\n\\n**Key Takeaways:**\\n\\n* The company offers various types of leave, including sick leave, FMLA, bereavement leave, parental leave, PTO, jury duty leave, and pregnancy leave.\\n* Employees must meet specific eligibility criteria for each type of leave, such as working for the company for more than 12 months or giving notice before their leave begins.\\n* The company offers support for new parents, including remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid daycare, and lactation rooms.\\n* Employees may be entitled to paid jury duty leave according to national law.\\n* The company will follow national law for jury duty leave and longer leave periods for pregnancy and parental leave.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-14 05:01:20.36511
