e22f1041-90fe-4792-b546-85df62c7ccd1	ca15452f-c7e2-4d0c-b078-0c2a08efeb71	summarization_tool	{"query": "summarize payroll policy", "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "**Payroll Policy Summary**\\n\\n**Document:** Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n1. **Purpose:** Establish a comprehensive and transparent framework for accurate, timely, and compliant processing of employee compensation.\\n2. **Scope:** Applies to all full-time and part-time employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees receiving stipends under Artemis supervision.\\n3. **Guiding Principles:**\\n\\t* Accuracy & Timeliness: Process payroll accurately and within the defined payroll calendar.\\n\\t* Confidentiality: Payroll information is strictly confidential and not to be disclosed to unauthorized individuals.\\n\\t* Compliance: Adhere to applicable labour laws, tax regulations, and statutory obligations governing employee compensation.\\n\\t* Transparency: Employees receive itemized payslips detailing all earnings, deductions, and net pay.\\n\\t* Equity & Non-Discrimination: Payroll processes are conducted in a fair and non-discriminatory manner.\\n\\t* Data Integrity: Payroll records are maintained securely and accurately with appropriate access controls and audit trails.\\n4. **Payroll Timelines:**\\n\\t* Salary disbursement: 29th of the current month\\n\\t* Payslip generation & distribution: Last working day of the month\\n\\t* Statutory filing (PF, ESI, PT, TDS): 1st working day of the following month\\n5. **Payroll Inputs:**\\n\\t* New joiner details\\n\\t* Separation details\\n\\t* Approved increment letters or salary revision notifications\\n\\t* Attendance records\\n\\t* Approved overtime claims and shift allowance details\\n6. **Statutory Compliance & Deductions:**\\n\\t* Employees' Provident Fund (EPF)\\n\\t* Employee State Insurance (ESI)\\n\\t* Professional Tax (PT)\\n\\t* Tax Deducted at Source (TDS)\\n\\t* Labour Welfare Fund (LWF)\\n\\t* Gratuity (Accrual & Payment)\\n7. **Payroll Confidentiality:**\\n\\t* Payroll data constitutes sensitive personal and financial information\\n\\t* Employees, managers, HR personnel, and Finance staff are bound by confidentiality obligations\\n8. **Record Keeping:**\\n\\t* Monthly Payroll Register: Retained for duration of employment + 8 years\\n\\t* Payslips (Employee Copies): Retained for duration of employment + 8 years\\n9. **Responsibilities:**\\n\\t* Employees: Submit accurate attendance, leave, investment declarations, and reimbursement claims on time\\n\\t* Managers/Supervisors: Approve attendance, overtime, leaves, and reimbursements within stipulated timelines\\n\\t* HR Business Partner: Submit payroll inputs, manage joiner/exit data, communicate policy to employees\\n\\t* HR Operations/Payroll Team: Process payroll accurately and on schedule; distribute payslips; manage statutory filings\\n\\t* Finance/Treasury: Approve payroll disbursement; manage statutory payments; maintain financial records\\n\\t* Legal/Compliance: Ensure adherence to applicable labour and tax laws; advise on statutory changes\\n10. **Payroll Grievance Redressal:**\\n\\t* Employees can raise a formal grievance through the HR Operations/Payroll team via the designated payroll helpdesk email or HRMS ticketing portal\\n\\t* The Payroll team will investigate the concern and provide a written response within 5 working days\\n\\t* If the employee is not satisfied with the resolution, the matter may be escalated to the HR Business Partner and subsequently to the HR Head for final resolution\\n\\n**Related Policy:** Employee Handbook (Section: Payroll)", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 2}	2026-04-14 05:14:32.926589
004b3216-016e-4a1b-9060-f8e19ecc5a13	63dfb4c4-3725-48c2-b8a4-8df22614990a	policy_retrieval_tool	{"query": "payroll [policy", "top_k": 5, "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided policy excerpts, here are the relevant rules related to payroll:\\n\\n* Employees are encouraged to contact the HR Division or designated payroll helpdesk for any clarifications regarding this policy (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* The Payroll team will investigate the concern and provide a written response within 5 working days (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* If an error is confirmed, the correction will be processed in the next available payroll cycle or through an off-cycle payment if the amount is significant (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* If the employee is not satisfied with the resolution, the matter may be escalated to the HR Business Partner and subsequently to the HR Head for final resolution (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* All escalations must be made in writing with supporting documentation (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* Employees who believe there is an error in their payroll computation or have concerns regarding deductions, reimbursements, or settlements may raise a formal grievance through the following process (Artemis_Payroll_Policy):\\n  • Step 1 — Raise a Query\\n  • Step 2 — Investigation\\n  • Step 3 — Escalation\\n* Breach of payroll confidentiality may attract disciplinary action as per the Company's Disciplinary Policy (HR-DP-001) (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* Access to payroll systems is role-based and governed by the IT Security Policy (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* The Payroll Policy will be reviewed annually or as necessitated by changes in applicable tax laws, labour regulations, statutory requirements, or organisational restructuring (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).\\n* Monthly Payroll Register and Payslips (Employee Copies) must be retained for the duration of employment + 8 years (Artemis_Payroll_Policy).", "chunks_count": 5, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-16 14:21:20.909779
d382b7cc-f9ae-425a-abe2-00cd1edd64de	726b1929-fc7d-4ed4-a619-e96d379433ec	summarization_tool	{"query": "culture", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Artemis Employee Handbook: Culture**\\n\\n**Summary:**\\n\\nThe Artemis Employee Handbook outlines the company's culture, values, and expectations for employees. The following points summarize the key aspects of the company's culture:\\n\\n**Our Culture**\\n\\n* The way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver.\\n* Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\\n* Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge.\\n* There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking.\\n* Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n\\n**Our Vision**\\n\\n* The company's mission is to unlock organizational potential through tailored strategic insights and dependable client support.\\n* The company sees itself as a long-term partner to its clients, not just a service provider.\\n\\n**Equal Opportunity Employment**\\n\\n* Artemis is an equal opportunity employer and does not tolerate discrimination against protected characteristics.\\n* The company commits to penalizing every discriminatory, offensive, or inappropriate behavior.\\n\\n**Workplace Culture**\\n\\n* The company encourages employees to treat others with respect and professionalism.\\n* Employees are expected to maintain professionalism and keep personal discussions outside of the workplace.\\n* The company prohibits fraternization, including dating or being friends with colleagues, to avoid accusations of favoritism, abuse of authority, and sexual harassment.\\n\\n**Employee Relationships**\\n\\n* The company encourages friendships between peers, but expects employees to focus on their work and keep personal disputes outside of the workplace.\\n* Employees are not allowed to date their managers or direct reports.\\n\\n**Conflicts of Interest**\\n\\n* Employees are expected to be vigilant to spot circumstances that create conflicts of interest, either to themselves or for their direct reports.\\n* Employees are expected to follow the company's policies and always act in the company's best interests.\\n\\n**Employee Development**\\n\\n* The company encourages employees to share their ideas and suggestions for improving the workplace.\\n* Employees are expected to maintain a high level of professionalism and adhere to the company's policies and procedures.\\n\\n**Acknowledgement**\\n\\n* Employees are required to sign an acknowledgement form to confirm that they have read and understood the employee handbook and are committed to following the company's policies.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 15:44:49.039468
