39ed1953-fa6c-4dae-85c3-2cfb16428954	78d74900-26a6-4270-8a2b-893041afb45e	policy_retrieval_tool	{"query": "tell me about recruitment policy at artemis", "top_k": 5, "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided policy excerpts, here are the key points about the recruitment policy at Artemis Technologies Pvt. Ltd.:\\n\\n**Objectives:**\\n• To recruit highly qualified and competent individuals  \\n• To ensure a fair, unbiased, and transparent hiring process  \\n• To promote diversity and inclusion within the organization  \\n• To maintain consistency and efficiency in recruitment practices  \\n• To align hiring decisions with organizational goals\\n\\n**Scope:**\\n• Compensation and benefits  \\n• Terms and conditions of employment  \\n• All stages of recruitment from job requirement identification to onboarding\\n\\n**Key Recruitment Activities:**\\n• Job requirement identification\\n• Defining the job role and responsibilities\\n• Identifying required technical and soft skills\\n• Determining experience level and qualifications\\n• Preparing a detailed job description\\n• Document verification\\n• Orientation sessions\\n• Introduction to company policies and culture\\n\\n**Equal Opportunity Policy:**\\n• Artemis Technologies Pvt. Ltd. is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all candidates.\\n• The company strictly prohibits discrimination based on:\\n  • Gender\\n  • Race\\n  • Religion\\n  • Nationality\\n  • Disability or background\\n\\n**Confidentiality:**\\n• All recruitment-related information must be handled with strict confidentiality.\\n• Candidate data must be securely stored and protected.", "chunks_count": 5, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-14 09:07:21.54003
4072f7c5-bca5-41c5-af33-ccfc656b2432	111a6a4b-5853-4593-a68c-9b67527a18d7	summarization_tool	{"query": "leave policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Leave Policy Summary**\\n\\n**Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n* **Eligible Employees:** Eligible employees can continue their group health benefits for a limited period after leaving the company under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA).\\n* **Sick Leave:**\\n\\t+ Inform manager and send a sick leave request through HRIS.\\n\\t+ Take a partial day off or work from home, but rest and recuperate for a day before returning to work.\\n\\t+ Use PTO or arrange for a flexible work schedule for routine health care appointments.\\n\\t+ Submit a physician's note or other medical certification and/or complete a sick leave form for insurance purposes if absent for more than 3 days.\\n* **Long-term Illness:**\\n\\t+ The U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act provides 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave for medical and family reasons.\\n\\t+ Eligible employees have worked for more than 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before the leave begins.\\n* **Bereavement Leave:**\\n\\t+ 3 days of paid bereavement leave to arrange a funeral or memorial service, attend a funeral or memorial service, resolve matters of inheritance, fulfill other family obligations, or mourn.\\n\\t+ 2 additional unpaid days off if traveling long-distance for a funeral or service.\\n* **Jury Duty and Voting:**\\n\\t+ Exempt employees can take 1 day of unpaid leave extension of up to 2 months for jury duty.\\n\\t+ Contact HR as soon as possible to arrange this.\\n* **Parental Leave:**\\n\\t+ Eligible employees can take up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave for medical and family reasons, including recovery from a serious health condition or caring for an immediate family member.\\n\\t+ Eligible employees have worked for more than 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before the leave begins.\\n\\t+ Returning to work after parental leave, the company offers remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid day care, and lactation rooms.\\n* **Resignation:**\\n\\t+ Resignation occurs when an employee voluntarily informs HR or their manager that they will stop working for the company.\\n\\t+ No advance notice is required, but it is recommended for efficiency's sake.\\n\\t+ Resigned employees may ask for references, and their manager has the right to oblige or refuse.\\n\\n**Main Rules:**\\n\\n* Eligible employees can continue their group health benefits under COBRA.\\n* Sick leave requires informing the manager and sending a sick leave request through HRIS.\\n* Long-term illness requires 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave under the U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act.\\n* Bereavement leave provides 3 days of paid leave and 2 additional unpaid days off for traveling long-distance.\\n* Jury duty and voting leave require contacting HR to arrange the leave.\\n* Parental leave provides up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave for medical and family reasons.\\n* Resignation requires informing HR or the manager that the employee will stop working for the company.\\n\\n**Critical Information:**\\n\\n* Eligible employees must have worked for more than 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before taking long-term illness or parental leave.\\n* Resigned employees may ask for references, but their manager has the right to oblige or refuse.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 04:30:17.096833
aaffaa11-b118-4225-b7e9-c7b68553beaa	ae8e43ff-1a2a-456c-a8d3-770fa7e2f3e3	policy_retrieval_tool	{"query": "leave policy", "top_k": 5, "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided policy excerpts, here are the relevant rules regarding leave policy:\\n\\n* If you are absent for more than three days of sick leave, you may need to provide a doctor's note and/or complete a sick leave form for insurance purposes. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)\\n* Eligible employees have access to an insurance package. For more information, contact HR. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)\\n* According to the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA), eligible employees may choose to continue their group health benefits for a limited period after leaving the company due to a qualifying event, such as termination for reasons other than gross misconduct and reduction in hours of employment. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)", "chunks_count": 5, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-16 04:42:56.55358
e33b544a-337c-4d80-bfe1-4a486212990f	78d74900-26a6-4270-8a2b-893041afb45e	policy_retrieval_tool	{"query": "tell me about payroll policy at artemis", "top_k": 5, "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided policy excerpts, here are the key points about the payroll policy at Artemis Technology Limited:\\n\\n**Scope:**\\n* Applies to all full-time and part-time employees, contract employees, consultants, interns, and trainees.\\n* Covers all departments, levels, and geographic locations.\\n\\n**Guiding Principles:**\\n* Accuracy & Timeliness (Document: Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf, Page: None)\\n\\n**Purpose:**\\n* Establishes a comprehensive and transparent framework for accurate, timely, and compliant processing of employee compensation.\\n* Ensures fair and consistent remuneration in accordance with contractual terms, statutory requirements, and internal compensation structures.\\n\\n**Payroll Grievance Redressal:**\\n* Employees can raise a formal grievance through the following process:\\n\\t+ Step 1: Raise a Query (within 7 working days of the salary credit date)\\n\\t+ Step 2: Investigation & Resolution (Payroll team will investigate and provide a written response within 5 working days)\\n\\n**Reimbursement Policy:**\\n* Claims must be submitted with original supporting receipts/invoices within 30 days of incurring the expense.\\n* Claims submitted after 30 days will not be entertained except with written approval from the Finance Head.\\n* All claims must be pre-approved by the employee's manager before submission.\\n* Approved reimbursements will be processed in the subsequent payroll cycle or within 7 working days via the expense module.\\n* Reimbursements are tax-exempt only where substantiated by valid bills and within prescribed limits.", "chunks_count": 5, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-14 09:14:34.43245
06f14ee6-85df-4337-b138-cbbb56e16d35	4b1ee7e5-f7e7-48f9-b6cd-7d78f8de84f8	summarization_tool	{"query": "culture at artemis", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Culture at Artemis**\\n\\n**Summary**\\n\\nThe culture at Artemis is built on the principles of collaboration, clarity, and accountability. The company encourages employees to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions. The emphasis is on making ideas understandable and actionable, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n* **Collaboration**: Teams are encouraged to collaborate and bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge.\\n* **Clarity**: There is a strong emphasis on clarity in communication and thinking.\\n* **Accountability**: Titles matter less than accountability, and employees are expected to take ownership of their contributions.\\n* **Recognition**: Good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n* **Company Values**: Artemis values teamwork, respect, and professionalism.\\n\\n**Policy Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 15:39:52.89415
de92497a-de37-42a5-b425-bc37422c9808	726b1929-fc7d-4ed4-a619-e96d379433ec	summarization_tool	{"query": "culture", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Artemis Employee Handbook: Culture**\\n\\n**Our Culture**\\n\\n* The way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver.\\n* Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\\n* Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge.\\n* There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking.\\n* Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n\\n**Our Vision**\\n\\n* Our mission is to unlock organizational potential through tailored strategic insights and dependable client support.\\n* We see Artemis as a long-term partner to our clients, not just a service provider.\\n\\n**Equal Opportunity Employment**\\n\\n* Artemis is an equal opportunity employer.\\n* We don't tolerate discrimination against protected characteristics (gender, age, sexual orientation, race, nationality, ethnicity, religion, disability, veteran status).\\n* We want all employees (including executives and HR) to treat others with respect and professionalism.\\n\\n**Diversity and Inclusion**\\n\\n* We commit to penalizing every discriminatory, offensive or inappropriate behavior.\\n* We ask you to report any discriminatory behavior.\\n* We conduct diversity and communication training.\\n\\n**Employee Relationships**\\n\\n* We want to ensure that relationships between employees are appropriate and harmonious.\\n* We outline our guidelines and ask you to always behave professionally.\\n* Fraternization refers to dating or being friends with your colleagues.\\n* Dating colleagues: maintain professionalism and keep personal discussions outside of the workplace.\\n* Dating managers: supervisors must not date their direct reports.\\n* Friendships at work: employees who work together may naturally form friendships, but we expect you to focus on your work and keep personal disputes outside of the workplace.\\n\\n**Employment of Relatives**\\n\\n* Everyone in our company should be hired, recognized or promoted because of their skills, character and work ethic.\\n* We would not like to see phenomena of nepotism, favoritism or conflicts of interest, so we will place some restrictions on hiring employees' relatives.\\n\\n**Solicitation and Distribution**\\n\\n* Solicitation is any form of requesting money, support or participation for products, groups, organizations or causes which are unrelated to our company.\\n* Distribution means disseminating literature or material for commercial or political purposes.\\n* We don't allow solicitation and distribution by non-employees in our workplace.\\n\\n**Compensation & Development**\\n\\n* In this section, we outline our guidelines for compensating employees according to their employment status.\\n* We also describe our performance management and employee development policies.\\n\\n**Employee Acknowledgement**\\n\\n* Please sign to acknowledge that you've read this handbook and that you are committed to following our policies.\\n* If you need any clarifications, feel free to ask HR.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 15:44:59.832255
