ot mentioned | Integrated with HRMS |  | Integration with HRMS |\\n| **Loss of Pay (LOP)** | Not mentioned | Applied in certain circumstances |  | Circumstances for LOP |\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n* Both policies mention the importance of fairness and equal opportunity.\\n* Both policies require employees to contact HR for any clarifications or concerns.\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n* The Leave Policy is not explicitly mentioned in the provided excerpts, while the Payroll Policy provides detailed information on leave-related topics.\\n* The Payroll Policy has a more comprehensive structure, including sections on attendance, leave, and loss of pay, while the Leave Policy is more general.\\n* The Payroll Policy has a more detailed process for Full & Final (F&F;) settlement, including leave encashment, while the Leave Policy does not mention this process.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 3}	2026-04-14 09:15:16.518575
