69c0e0e7-c2cf-4dcf-a40d-97357e722c2c	bdd02ecd-e643-4a14-95ab-316eca0f0644	summarization_tool	{"query": "summarize the leave policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Leave Policy Summary**\\n\\n**Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n* **Paid Time Off (PTO):** Employees are entitled to PTO, but the number of days is not specified.\\n* **Holidays:** Hours worked on a holiday will be counted to decide whether overtime pay is due.\\n* **Sick Leave:** Employees are offered [one week] of paid sick leave. In states or countries where employees are entitled to a greater number of sick leave days by law, the company will follow that law.\\n* **Long-term Illness:** The U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act provides employees 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave in a 12-month period with the same group health benefits for medical and family reasons.\\n* **Bereavement Leave:** An unpaid leave extension of up to [two months] may be granted for bereavement.\\n* **Parental Leave:** Employees may take parental leave, and the company offers remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid daycare, and lactation rooms to help new parents transition back to work.\\n* **Jury Duty Leave:** National law obliges the company to provide hourly employees with paid jury duty leave.\\n* **Voting Leave:** National law stipulates longer leave, and the company will follow the law.\\n* **Pregnancy and Childbirth Leave:** Pregnant women can take part of their leave before labor, and an unpaid leave extension of up to [two months] may be granted for complications during childbirth or other issues.\\n\\n**Main Rules:**\\n\\n* Employees must give at least [three months] notice before their parental leave begins.\\n* Employees may take sick leave to recover from short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, and other indisposition.\\n* Employees must inform their manager and send a sick leave request through the HRIS if they become sick.\\n* Employees may take a partial day off or work from home while sick, but are advised to rest and recuperate for a day before returning to work.\\n\\n**Critical Information:**\\n\\n* Employees are eligible for long-term illness leave if they have worked for the company for more than 12 months and have worked at least 1,250 hours within 12 months before their leave begins.\\n* Employees may be entitled to accrued vacation and sick leave upon termination, depending on local law.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 12:13:57.266842
