e5d6f714-ec61-41c3-9f4b-2177c89df5ff	6fcc3709-440d-4212-8303-77656b5d2d48	summarization_tool	{"query": "leave policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Leave Policy Summary**\\n\\n**Document:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n\\n* **Eligible Employees:** Eligible employees can continue their group health benefits for a limited period after leaving the company under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA).\\n* **Sick Leave:**\\n\\t+ Inform manager and send a sick leave request through HRIS.\\n\\t+ Take a partial day off or work from home.\\n\\t+ Rest and recuperate for a day before returning to work.\\n\\t+ Use PTO or arrange for a flexible work schedule for routine healthcare appointments.\\n* **Long-term Illness:**\\n\\t+ Eligible for 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave under the U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA) for medical and family reasons.\\n\\t+ Must have worked for the company for more than 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before leave begins.\\n* **Bereavement Leave:**\\n\\t+ 3 days of paid bereavement leave for arranging a funeral or memorial service, attending a funeral or memorial service, resolving matters of inheritance, fulfilling other family obligations, or mourning.\\n\\t+ 2 additional unpaid days off for traveling long-distance for a funeral or service.\\n* **Jury Duty and Voting:**\\n\\t+ Exempt employees can take 1 day of unpaid leave extension of up to 2 months.\\n\\t+ Contact HR as soon as possible to arrange this.\\n* **Parental Leave:**\\n\\t+ Eligible for 12 weeks of unpaid, job-protected leave under the U.S. Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA) for medical and family reasons.\\n\\t+ Must have worked for the company for more than 12 months and 1,250 hours within 12 months before leave begins.\\n\\t+ Offered remote working, flexible hours, onsite/external paid daycare, and lactation rooms for new parents transitioning back to work.\\n* **Leaving the Company:**\\n\\t+ Employment is \\"at-will\\" in the U.S., meaning the company or employee can terminate the employment relationship at any time and for any non-discriminatory reason.\\n\\t+ May be entitled to compensation for accrued vacation and sick leave upon termination, depending on local law.\\n\\t+ May receive references upon termination or resignation in good standing.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 06:44:07.075936
