1a748f9a-13ac-41a4-9ece-1d376078b492	bdd02ecd-e643-4a14-95ab-316eca0f0644	policy_retrieval_tool	{"query": "tell me about the culture at artemis", "top_k": 5, "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided policy excerpts from the \\"artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\" document, the culture at Artemis is described as follows:\\n\\n* The way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver (Our Culture).\\n* Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions (Our Culture).\\n* Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge (Our Culture).\\n* There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking (Our Culture).\\n* Titles matter less than accountability (Our Culture).\\n* Good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility (Our Culture and Our Vision).\\n\\nThese points highlight the importance of teamwork, collaboration, clarity, and accountability in the Artemis culture.", "chunks_count": 5, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-16 12:14:25.334509
6b0a1295-591d-4fd1-ba28-a5352666e2be	bdd02ecd-e643-4a14-95ab-316eca0f0644	comparison_tool	{"query": "compare sick leave and paid time off", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Sick Leave and Paid Time Off (PTO)**\\n\\n**Policy Documents:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n| Feature | Sick Leave | Paid Time Off (PTO) |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Accrual | Begins on the day of joining the company | Begins on the day of joining the company |\\n| Use | Can be taken at any time after the first week with the company | Can be taken at any time after the first week with the company |\\n| Request | Must be sent through HRIS | Must be sent through HRIS |\\n| Manager Approval | Required | Required |\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| Feature | Sick Leave | Paid Time Off (PTO) |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Duration | 1 week | Up to 25 days (20 days + 5 additional days after 1 year) |\\n| Purpose | Short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, and other indisposition | Vacation, personal days, and other non-medical reasons |\\n| Use of PTO | Can use PTO for sick leave, but not the other way around | Can use PTO for sick leave, but not the other way around |\\n| Additional Benefits | Long-term illness and parental leave policies | Holiday pay, floating days, and remote working/flexible hours |\\n| Cap | No cap | 25 days overall |\\n| Accrual Rate | 1.7 days per month | 1.7 days per month (increases by 1 day per year after the first year) |\\n| Carryover | Can transfer remaining PTO to the next year | Can transfer remaining PTO to the next year |\\n\\n**Additional Notes:**\\n\\n* Sick leave is only available for short-term illnesses, while PTO can be used for vacation, personal days, and other non-medical reasons.\\n* PTO has a cap of 25 days overall, while sick leave does not have a cap.\\n* PTO accrual rate increases by 1 day per year after the first year, while sick leave accrual rate is not mentioned.\\n* PTO can be used for holiday pay, floating days, and remote working/flexible hours, while sick leave is only available for short-term illnesses.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 06:45:20.994014
9c432f49-47a6-4fef-85f3-9640bad20bb3	bdd02ecd-e643-4a14-95ab-316eca0f0644	comparison_tool	{"query": "compare the sick leave and paid time off policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Sick Leave and Paid Time Off (PTO) Policies**\\n\\n**Document Names:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Comparison Focus:** Sick Leave and Paid Time Off (PTO) Policies\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n| Policy | Sick Leave | PTO |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Accrual | Begins on the day of joining the company | Begins on the day of joining the company |\\n| Accrual Rate | Not specified | 1.7 days per month |\\n| Maximum Accrual | Not specified | 25 days overall |\\n| Use of Accrued Time | Can be used at any time after the first week | Can be used at any time after the first week |\\n| Transfer of Accrued Time | Can be transferred to the next year | Can be transferred to the next year |\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| Policy | Sick Leave | PTO |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Number of Days | 1 week (or more, depending on local law) | 20 days per year (with a cap of 25 days) |\\n| Purpose | To recover from short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, and other indisposition | For vacation, personal, or family reasons |\\n| Request Process | Send a sick leave request through HRIS | Send a PTO request through HRIS |\\n| Manager Approval | Required | Required |\\n| Use of PTO for Sick Leave | Can use PTO for sick leave, but advised to use sick leave instead | Can use PTO for sick leave |\\n| Physician's Note | May be required for absences of more than 3 days | Not specified |\\n| Overtime Pay | Not specified | Hours worked on a holiday may be counted towards overtime pay |\\n\\n**Note:** The policies have some overlap, and the company may follow local laws regarding sick leave. The PTO policy has a more detailed accrual process and a cap on the maximum accrual.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 06:47:41.461235
8e1164b1-5a8f-414b-9cd4-82399bb01cb7	a43f2bcc-78f3-41c0-8169-3bc49031bc7e	comparison_tool	{"query": "compare between payroll and leave policy", "user_role": "HR"}	{"answer": "**Comparison between Payroll and Leave Policy**\\n\\n**Policy Documents:**\\n- Artemis_Payroll_Policy (1).pdf\\n- artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Comparison Table:**\\n\\n| **Category** | **Payroll Policy** | **Leave Policy** | **Similarities** | **Differences** |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n| **Salary Disbursement** | Monthly by bank transfers | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n| **Attendance Tracking** | Integrated with HRMS | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n| **Leave Encashment** | Encashment of unused EL balance | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n| **Gratuity** | Payable upon completion of 5 years | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n| **Record Keeping** | Monthly Payroll Register: Duration of employment + 8 years | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n| **Policy Review** | Annual review or as necessitated by changes | Annual revision of handbook |  |  |\\n| **Confidentiality** | Payroll data constitutes sensitive personal and financial information | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n| **Escalation Process** | Escalation to HR Business Partner and HR Head | Not mentioned |  |  |\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n- Both policies are reviewed annually or as necessitated by changes.\\n- Both policies have a record-keeping component.\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n- Salary disbursement is mentioned in the Payroll Policy, but not in the Leave Policy.\\n- Attendance tracking is integrated with HRMS in the Payroll Policy, but not mentioned in the Leave Policy.\\n- Leave encashment is mentioned in the Payroll Policy, but not in the Leave Policy.\\n- Gratuity is payable upon completion of 5 years in the Payroll Policy, but not mentioned in the Leave Policy.\\n- Record keeping is mentioned in the Payroll Policy, but not in the Leave Policy.\\n- Confidentiality is mentioned in the Payroll Policy, but not in the Leave Policy.\\n- Escalation process is mentioned in the Payroll Policy, but not in the Leave Policy.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 2}	2026-04-16 06:48:38.02914
2733775c-accc-4098-8d54-4b7ae303b245	94986a10-33ea-433f-926a-1c8fe1583385	policy_retrieval_tool	{"query": "leave policy", "top_k": 5, "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "Based on the provided policy excerpts, here are the relevant rules regarding leave policy:\\n\\n* If you are absent for more than three days of sick leave, you may need to provide a doctor's note and/or complete a sick leave form for insurance purposes. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)\\n* Eligible employees have access to an insurance package. For more information, contact HR. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)\\n* According to the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA), eligible employees may choose to continue their group health benefits for a limited period after leaving the company due to a qualifying event, such as termination for reasons other than gross misconduct and reduction in hours of employment. (Document: artemis_employee_handbook.pdf, Page: None)", "chunks_count": 5, "sources_count": 5}	2026-04-16 06:50:51.62764
