d7f89e5a-8468-4d51-b8bd-6fb466dfc008	94986a10-33ea-433f-926a-1c8fe1583385	summarization_tool	{"query": "summarize culture at artemis", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Summary of Culture at Artemis**\\n\\n**Our Culture**\\n\\n* The way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver.\\n* Teams are encouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their contributions.\\n* Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to bring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge.\\n* There is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking.\\n* Titles matter less than accountability, and good work is recognized through impact rather than visibility.\\n\\n**Our Vision**\\n\\n* Our mission is to unlock organizational potential through tailored strategic insights and dependable client support.\\n* We see Artemis as a long-term partner to our clients, not just a service provider.\\n\\n**Employee Relationships**\\n\\n* We want to ensure that relationships between employees are appropriate and harmonious.\\n* We outline our guidelines and ask employees to always behave professionally.\\n* Fraternization refers to dating or being friends with your colleagues.\\n* Non-consensual romantic relationships are not allowed.\\n* Friendships at work are encouraged, but personal disputes should be kept outside of the workplace.\\n\\n**Employment of Relatives**\\n\\n* We would not like to see phenomena of nepotism, favoritism or conflicts of interest, so we will place some restrictions on hiring employees' relatives.\\n\\n**Employee Training and Development**\\n\\n* We invest in our employees' professional development to show our gratitude for their hard work.\\n* Each employee has $1,000 annually to spend on educational activities or material.\\n* We offer online courses and other training opportunities to help employees improve their efficiency and productivity.\\n\\n**Benefits and Perks**\\n\\n* We provide information on our health insurance plans and benefits like work from home options and company-issued equipment.\\n* Employee health is important to us, and we don't discriminate against people with disabilities or health conditions.\\n\\n**Employee Acknowledgement**\\n\\n* Please sign to acknowledge that you've read this handbook and that you are committed to following our policies.\\n* If you need any clarifications, feel free to ask HR.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 06:51:20.641847
