884d9bfe-8784-44ba-b07c-ff35f9299a5c	bdd02ecd-e643-4a14-95ab-316eca0f0644	comparison_tool	{"query": "compare the sick leave and paid time off policy", "user_role": "Employee"}	{"answer": "**Comparison of Sick Leave and Paid Time Off (PTO) Policies**\\n\\n**Policy Documents:** artemis_employee_handbook.pdf\\n\\n**Comparison Focus:** Sick Leave and Paid Time Off (PTO) Policies\\n\\n**Similarities:**\\n\\n| Policy | Sick Leave | PTO |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Accrual | Begins on the day of joining the company | Begins on the day of joining the company |\\n| Accrual Rate | Not specified | 1.7 days per month |\\n| Maximum Accrual | Not specified | 25 days overall |\\n| Use of Accrued Time | Can be used at any time after the first week with the company | Can be used at any time after the first week with the company |\\n| Carryover | Can be transferred to the next year | Can be transferred to the next year |\\n\\n**Differences:**\\n\\n| Policy | Sick Leave | PTO |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Number of Days | 1 week (or more in states/countries with greater entitlement) | 20 days per year (with a cap of 25 days overall) |\\n| Purpose | To recover from short-term illness, injuries, mental issues, and other indisposition | For vacation, personal, or family reasons |\\n| Request Process | Send a sick leave request through HRIS | Send a PTO request through HRIS |\\n| Manager Approval | Required | Required |\\n| Use of PTO for Sick Leave | Can use PTO for sick leave, but advised to use sick leave for contagious diseases | Can use PTO for sick leave, but advised to use sick leave for contagious diseases |\\n| Physician's Note | May be required for absences of more than 3 days | Not specified |\\n| Carryover of Unused Time | Can be transferred to the next year | Can be transferred to the next year |\\n\\n**Additional Notes:**\\n\\n* The company offers a floating day, which can be taken as a holiday on any day chosen.\\n* Exempt employees receive their normal compensation without any deductions on holidays, while non-exempt employees receive their regular hourly rate with a premium for working on a holiday.\\n* The company will count hours worked on a holiday to decide whether an employee is entitled to overtime pay.", "chunks_count": 20, "sources_count": 1}	2026-04-16 06:51:50.610943
