12cff9e8-1e50-466c-9c81-a541ca371fba	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	0	RECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION POLICY   |   Artemis | Human Resources \n& Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Page 1 \nRECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION \nPOLICY \nArtemis | Human Resources & Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Last Reviewed: April 2025   |   Approved \nBy: Chief Human Resources Officer, Artemis \n1. PURPOSE \nThis Records Management & Administration Policy establishes a structured framework for the \ncreation, classification, storage, retrieval, retention, and disposal of all internal and \nadministrative documents at Artemis. The objective of this policy is to ensure that organizational	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
1c8b6120-bb5d-4494-8d7d-267a3aadd2b6	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	1	administrative documents at Artemis. The objective of this policy is to ensure that organizational \nrecords are accurately maintained, readily accessible to authorized personnel, and managed in \ncompliance with applicable legal and regulatory requirements. \n \nArtemis recognizes that well-managed records are fundamental to operational efficiency, \ninformed decision-making, and institutional accountability. This policy applies to all physical and \ndigital records generated or received in the course of Artemis business operations. \n2. SCOPE \nThis policy applies to: \n• All full-time and part-time employees of Artemis \n• Contract employees, consultants, and third-party service providers generating or \nmanaging Artemis records	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
174fcc47-ccfa-445f-836a-26c10a79d7ba	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	2	• Contract employees, consultants, and third-party service providers generating or \nmanaging Artemis records \n• Interns and trainees handling official documents under Artemis supervision \n• All departments, business units, and office locations of Artemis \n \nThis policy governs records in all formats including paper documents, electronic files, emails, \nspreadsheets, presentations, audio-visual materials, and records stored on cloud platforms or \nthird-party systems. \n3. GUIDING PRINCIPLES \nArtemis adheres to the following principles in all records management and administrative \nmatters: \n \n3.1 Accuracy & Completeness \nAll records must be accurate, complete, and created contemporaneously with the events or	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
f481c492-c7c2-4b22-9bd6-b7d36108312c	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	3	matters: \n \n3.1 Accuracy & Completeness \nAll records must be accurate, complete, and created contemporaneously with the events or \ntransactions they document. Retroactive alterations or omissions are strictly prohibited. \n3.2 Accessibility \nRecords must be stored and organized such that authorized personnel can locate and retrieve \nthem promptly. Inaccessible or disorganized records undermine organizational effectiveness.	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
eb9a4fab-53af-4119-a6c9-10a029477ce4	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	4	RECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION POLICY   |   Artemis | Human Resources \n& Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Page 2 \n3.3 Security & Confidentiality \nRecords containing sensitive, personal, or proprietary information must be protected against \nunauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction at all times. \n3.4 Retention & Disposal \nRecords must be retained for the minimum period required by law and organizational need, then \ndisposed of securely and in accordance with this policy. \n3.5 Compliance \nRecords management practices must comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and statutory \nrequirements, including labor laws, tax regulations, and data protection legislation. \n3.6 Accountability	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
9918e82f-697b-4d84-a6f7-c00e81dee994	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	5	requirements, including labor laws, tax regulations, and data protection legislation. \n3.6 Accountability \nEvery employee is responsible for the records they create and manage. Custodianship of \nrecords is formally assigned to designated roles within each department. \n4. CATEGORIES OF ORGANIZATIONAL RECORDS  \n4.1 Human Resources Records \nRecords related to the employment lifecycle of individuals at Artemis. This includes: \n• Offer letters, employment contracts, and amendments \n• Onboarding documents, background verification reports, and identity proofs \n• Performance appraisal records, promotion letters, and transfer orders \n• Leave records, attendance registers, and payroll documentation \n• Disciplinary records, warnings, and investigation reports	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
dad307ec-33cd-4fe9-b456-ed2e035ba079	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	6	• Leave records, attendance registers, and payroll documentation \n• Disciplinary records, warnings, and investigation reports \n• Separation documents, exit interview records, and full & final settlement details \n4.2 Financial & Accounting Records \nRecords related to the financial transactions, reporting, and compliance obligations of Artemis. \nThis includes: \n• Invoices, purchase orders, payment receipts, and expense reimbursements \n• Bank statements, account reconciliations, and ledger entries \n• Statutory filings including TDS, GST, provident fund, and ESI records \n• Audit reports, financial statements, and budget documents \n• Vendor contracts and service agreements with financial implications \n4.3 Legal & Compliance Records	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
97a61e6b-06de-431e-b739-7c3e7e6d2d4b	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	7	• Vendor contracts and service agreements with financial implications \n4.3 Legal & Compliance Records \nRecords pertaining to legal obligations, regulatory compliance, and governance. This includes: \n• Corporate registration documents, licenses, and statutory certificates \n• Board resolutions, shareholder agreements, and meeting minutes \n• Legal correspondence, court filings, and settlement agreements \n• Compliance certificates, regulatory submissions, and audit correspondence	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
f2f831cd-452c-4a50-9a82-9d51c6100027	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	8	RECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION POLICY   |   Artemis | Human Resources \n& Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Page 3 \n• Intellectual property filings, trademarks, and patents \n4.4 Operational & Administrative Records \nRecords relating to the day-to-day operations and administration of Artemis. This includes: \n• Internal communications including memos, circulars, and notices \n• Project documentation, meeting minutes, and task records \n• IT asset registers, procurement records, and facility management logs \n• Travel authorizations, accommodation records, and business expense approvals \n• Training records, certification logs, and development plans \n4.5 Client & Stakeholder Records	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
06eb7a94-9b3f-4113-a115-c4769272b39e	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	9	• Training records, certification logs, and development plans \n4.5 Client & Stakeholder Records \nRecords relating to external parties with whom Artemis has formal or commercial relationships. \nThis includes: \n• Client contracts, proposals, and engagement letters \n• Correspondence with regulators, auditors, and government bodies \n• Partnership agreements, MoUs, and non-disclosure agreements \n• Customer feedback, complaint logs, and resolution records \n5. DOCUMENT LIFECYCLE MANAGEMENT \n5.1 Creation \nAll official records must be created using authorized templates, formats, and naming \nconventions approved by the Administration Division. Documents must include: \n• Document title and unique reference number or code \n• Date of creation or last revision	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
