b4bf18ec-bcf8-4f49-acbf-840567692937	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	12	RECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION POLICY   |   Artemis | Human Resources \n& Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Page 4 \nFor documents subject to revision (e.g., policies, contracts, procedures), version control must be \nmaintained: \n• Major revisions increment the primary version number (v1.0 to v2.0) \n• Minor revisions increment the secondary version number (v1.0 to v1.1) \n• Superseded versions must be archived and clearly labeled as 'Obsolete' \n• Only the current approved version may be distributed or acted upon \n5.4 Retrieval \nAuthorized personnel may retrieve records through the document management system or by \nsubmitting a written request to the departmental records custodian. Retrieval requests will be	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
f3dc6cbd-6b1f-4d6c-8d32-33327d6bd7d9	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	13	submitting a written request to the departmental records custodian. Retrieval requests will be \nfulfilled within 2 working days for routine requests and within 4 working hours for urgent \noperational needs. \n5.5 Disposal \nRecords must not be disposed of before the expiry of the retention period specified in Section 8. \nUpon expiry: \n• Physical records must be shredded using a cross-cut shredder or disposed of through a \ncertified document destruction service \n• Electronic records must be permanently deleted using approved data sanitization \nmethods; standard deletion is insufficient \n• A disposal log must be maintained for all records destroyed, recording the document \ntype, date of destruction, and authorizing officer \n6. DOCUMENT CLASSIFICATION \nClassification Level Description Access	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
7b6d445c-41de-407c-a4c2-143f8213c9f7	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	14	type, date of destruction, and authorizing officer \n6. DOCUMENT CLASSIFICATION \nClassification Level Description Access \nPublic Approved for external audiences \nwith no restriction \nAll employees and general \npublic \nInternal Use Only For general internal circulation; \nnot for external sharing \nAll Artemis employees \nConfidential Sensitive business or personal \ninformation requiring controlled \naccess \nAuthorized employees on a \nneed-to-know basis \nRestricted / Classified Highly sensitive information \nsubject to strictest controls \nNamed individuals or specific \nroles only; requires explicit \nauthorization \n \nAll documents must be clearly marked with their classification level on the header, footer, or	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
02878bc2-4280-4328-8786-668e3d8be67e	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	15	roles only; requires explicit \nauthorization \n \nAll documents must be clearly marked with their classification level on the header, footer, or \ncover page. Documents containing a mix of classification levels default to the highest applicable \nclassification. \n7. ADMINISTRATIVE DOCUMENT PROCEDURES	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
0d513eea-a4f0-4039-b7fb-2f21ae4ee7d9	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	16	RECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION POLICY   |   Artemis | Human Resources \n& Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Page 5 \n7.1 Correspondence Management \nAll official inward and outward correspondence must be logged in the central correspondence \nregister maintained by the Administration Division. Inward correspondence must be \nacknowledged within 2 working days. Outward correspondence must be authorized by the \nrelevant department head before dispatch. \n7.2 Policy & Procedure Documents \nAll organizational policies and standard operating procedures (SOPs) must be: \n• Drafted using the standard Artemis policy template \n• Reviewed and approved by the relevant department head and HR/Legal prior to release	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
23273a5e-dc46-47af-86f3-5c22097b86e1	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	17	• Drafted using the standard Artemis policy template \n• Reviewed and approved by the relevant department head and HR/Legal prior to release \n• Published through official HR or Administration channels with an effective date \n• Reviewed at least annually or upon any material change in law or organizational \nstructure \n• Acknowledged by all employees to whom they apply within 30 days of release or update \n7.3 Contract Management \nAll contracts, agreements, and MoUs entered into on behalf of Artemis must be: \n• Reviewed by the Legal/Compliance Division prior to execution \n• Signed only by authorized signatories as defined in the Delegation of Authority matrix \n• Stored in the centralized contracts repository with a tracking number, counterparty \nname, key dates, and value	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
ef8d4112-6002-431e-914e-7526d2606684	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	18	• Stored in the centralized contracts repository with a tracking number, counterparty \nname, key dates, and value \n• Reviewed 90 days before expiry for renewal, renegotiation, or termination decisions \n7.4 Meeting Documentation \nMinutes must be prepared for all formal internal meetings including board meetings, \nmanagement review meetings, and departmental reviews. Minutes must be: \n• Drafted within 48 hours of the meeting \n• Circulated to all attendees and relevant stakeholders for review \n• Approved and signed by the chairperson within 5 working days \n• Filed in the appropriate departmental or board records folder \n8. RECORD RETENTION SCHEDULE \nRecord Category Specific Record Type Retention Period \nHR Records Employment contracts & offer \nletters \nDuration of employment \n+ 7 years	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
