f73bf915-ad8d-4fa7-aead-94961787a8c5	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	22	beyond the standard retention period until the matter is formally concluded, regardless of the \nschedule above. \n9. RESPONSIBILITIES \nRole Responsibility \nEmployee Create accurate records; file documents promptly; maintain \nconfidentiality; comply with retention and disposal rules \nDepartment Records \nCustodian \nOversee departmental filing; manage retrieval requests; \nconduct periodic records audits; coordinate disposal \nHR Division Maintain all employment-related records; enforce policy \ncompliance; manage personnel files	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
3efd8279-f22d-4e4e-9f77-799b89c762f4	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	23	RECORDS MANAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION POLICY   |   Artemis | Human Resources \n& Administration Division \nPolicy Code: HR-ADP-003   |   Version: 1.0   |   Effective Date: April 2025   |   Page 7 \nRole Responsibility \nAdministration Division Maintain centralized document management system; manage \ncorrespondence register; coordinate cross-departmental \nrecords \nLegal / Compliance Maintain legal and regulatory records; advise on statutory \nretention requirements; manage litigation holds \nFinance Division Maintain financial records; ensure compliance with statutory \nretention requirements for tax and audit records \nIT Division Maintain digital records infrastructure; enforce electronic \nrecords security; manage backup and recovery systems	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
063c6dde-0316-483f-bb64-936d42d5dea2	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	24	IT Division Maintain digital records infrastructure; enforce electronic \nrecords security; manage backup and recovery systems \nSenior Management Approve disposal of Restricted records; sign off on policy \ndocuments; ensure organizational compliance \n10. AUDIT & COMPLIANCE \nThe Administration Division, in coordination with HR and Legal, will conduct a records \nmanagement audit at least once per year. The audit will assess: \n• Completeness and accuracy of records across all departments \n• Compliance with filing, classification, and naming standards \n• Adherence to retention and disposal schedules \n• Security of physical and digital records \n• Effectiveness of access controls and retrieval procedures	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
06c2d032-8383-40d3-a052-55744e1678ba	43599a4a-e7e2-49fe-85e7-f610998bb594	25	• Security of physical and digital records \n• Effectiveness of access controls and retrieval procedures \n \nDepartments found to be non-compliant will be required to submit a corrective action plan within \n15 working days of receiving the audit report. Repeated non-compliance may result in \nescalation under the Disciplinary Policy (HR-DP-001). \n11. VIOLATIONS & DISCIPLINARY ACTION \nViolations of this policy will be addressed in accordance with the Artemis Disciplinary Policy \n(HR-DP-001). The following actions constitute serious breaches of this policy and may result in \ndisciplinary action up to and including termination: \n• Deliberate destruction or falsification of official records \n• Unauthorized access to, modification of, or disclosure of Confidential or Restricted \ndocuments	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
