88cac323-28ac-4064-8ff7-0391d79d1d60	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	3	Welcome \nHello and welcome! Thank you for joining Artemis, where we strive to unlock organizational \npotential through tailored strategic insights and unparalleled client support. We can’t wait to see \nwhat you will achieve with us. \nThis employee handbook defines who we are and how we work together. We will do \neverything possible to create a fair and productive workplace, but we need your help. \nWe’ve created this handbook to guide you. \nThis handbook isn’t a contract or a guarantee of employment. It’s a collection of our \nexpectations, commitments and responsibilities. Please read this employee handbook \ncarefully and consult it whenever you need to. \n \nGetting to know our company \nArtemis was founded with a simple observation: many organizations struggle not	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
881673d4-7343-40e0-bb83-474a46609c71	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	4	Getting to know our company \nArtemis was founded with a simple observation: many organizations struggle not \nbecause they lack ambition, but because they lack clarity. In its early days, the \ncompany operated as a small advisory group, working closely with a handful of clients \nto untangle operational challenges and provide structured direction. What began as a \nfocused effort to support decision-making has grown into a broader enterprise \ndedicated to helping organizations better understand themselves and act with intention. \nToday, Artemis works across industries, supporting leaders in translating complex \nsituations into practical strategies. While the scope of our work has expanded, the \napproach remains consistent—listen carefully, think rigorously, and follow through with	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
012dbf83-4297-4399-8955-f618cca23043	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	5	approach remains consistent—listen carefully, think rigorously, and follow through with \ndependable support. \nOur Culture \nAt Artemis, the way we work matters as much as the outcomes we deliver. Teams are \nencouraged to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and take ownership of their \ncontributions. Collaboration is deliberate rather than automatic; people are expected to \nbring their perspective, but also to adapt when better ideas emerge. \nThere is a strong emphasis on clarity—both in communication and in thinking. Whether \ndrafting a report or leading a client discussion, employees are expected to make their \nideas understandable and actionable. Titles matter less than accountability, and good \nwork is recognized through impact rather than visibility. \nOur Vision	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
ad4dd8fb-78f2-4546-8f71-a93d1b9226a6	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	6	work is recognized through impact rather than visibility. \nOur Vision \nOur mission is to unlock organizational potential through tailored strategic insights and \ndependable client support. In practice, this means helping organizations move from \nuncertainty to direction, and from direction to measurable progress. \nWe see Artemis as a long-term partner to our clients, not just a service provider. The	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
74fed679-fda9-4b57-8fb2-0fa8837b74c7	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	7	goal is not only to solve immediate challenges, but to leave organizations better \nequipped to handle what comes next. \n \nEmployment basics \nIn this section, we explain our employee contract types and define our basic \nemployment policies. \n \nEmployment contract types \nFull-time employees work at least 30 hours per week or 130 hours per month on \naverage. \n \nPart-time employees are those who work fewer than 30 hours per week. \n \nFull-time and part-time employees can have either temporary or indefinite duration \ncontracts. Full-time employees under an indefinite duration contract are entitled to our \ncompany’s full benefits package. \n \nWe remind you that, in the U.S., employment is “at-will.” This means that you or our	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
b5ef04a1-24fa-4cb6-a081-bb4ebd57cdb9	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	8	company’s full benefits package. \n \nWe remind you that, in the U.S., employment is “at-will.” This means that you or our \ncompany may terminate our employment relationship at any time and for any non-\ndiscriminatory reason(s). \n \nEqual opportunity employment \nArtemis is an equal opportunity employer. We don’t tolerate discrimination against \nprotected characteristics (gender, age, sexual orientation, race, nationality, ethnicity, \nreligion, disability, veteran status.) We want all employees (including executives and \nHR) to treat others with respect and professionalism. In practice, this means that we: \n \n■ [Hire and promote people based on skills, experience or potential and try to \nreduce bias in every process (e.g. through structured interviews.)]	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
0ffecbcd-a684-4601-a8c3-518b91d58775	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	9	reduce bias in every process (e.g. through structured interviews.)] \n \n■ [Make accommodations to help people with disabilities move about safely on our \npremises and use our products, services and equipment.] \n \n■ [Use inclusive, diversity-sensitive language in all official documents, signs and job \nads.] \n \n■ [Conduct diversity and communication training.] \n \n \nApart from those actions, we commit to penalizing every discriminatory, offensive or \ninappropriate behavior. To do this properly, we ask you to report any discriminatory	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
dfb9fdca-647e-420d-9979-d147f8183021	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	10	action against yourself or your colleagues to HR. Our company will not retaliate against \nyou if you file a complaint or discrimination lawsuit. Any employee who retaliates or \ndiscriminates will face disciplinary action. \n \n \n \nRecruitment and selection process \nOur hiring steps might vary across roles, but we always aim for a process that is fair and \neffective in hiring great people. If you are hiring for an open role, you will likely go \nthrough these steps: \n \ni. Identify the need for a new job opening. \nii. Decide whether to hire externally or internally. \niii. Review job descriptions and write a job ad. \niv. Get approval for your job ad. \nv. Select appropriate sources (external or internal) to post your job opening. \nvi. Decide on hiring stages and possible timeframes.	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
49f177f3-41c2-4613-8c87-b62ad59f1c8f	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	11	v. Select appropriate sources (external or internal) to post your job opening. \nvi. Decide on hiring stages and possible timeframes. \nvii. Review resumes in our company database/ATS. \nviii. Source passive candidates. \nix. Shortlist applicants. \nx. Screen and interview candidates. \nxi. Run background checks and check references. \nxii. Select the most suitable candidate. \nxiii. Make an official offer. \n \nSteps may overlap, so skip steps when appropriate. Each member of a hiring team \nmight have different responsibilities (e.g. recruiters source and hiring managers \ninterview candidates.) \n \nThroughout this process, we aim to keep candidates informed, communicate well with \neach other and give everyone an equal opportunity to work with us. Ask our recruiters	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
cc27af18-a33b-4952-9c01-419621bd9fc5	c5cac33e-d683-42e5-a870-f56bd795e9d7	12	each other and give everyone an equal opportunity to work with us. Ask our recruiters \nfor help whenever you need to enhance candidate experience or write an inclusive job \ndescription. \n \nBackground checks \nIf you want to run background checks on candidates, ask HR for guidance. This process \nis sensitive and we must always abide by laws and ensure candidates understand our \nintentions. As a general rule, commission a background check for finalists only. Use our \ncontracted provider and ensure you have your candidates’ permission. \n \n \nReferrals \nIf you know someone who you think would be a good fit for a position at our company,	\N	2026-04-10 09:48:05.090797
